{"type":"user","uuid":"e046ca5e-1e0d-4d8f-9da5-ccf3e056f374","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde65adb04db22eab291f578d5bcf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n   2→MODULE: pipeline\n   3→PATH: dev-pipeline/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: automation scripts + templates for feature/bugfix pipelines\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- dev-pipeline/run.sh\n   8→- dev-pipeline/run-bugfix.sh\n   9→- dev-pipeline/launch-daemon.sh\n  10→- dev-pipeline/launch-bugfix-daemon.sh\n  11→- dev-pipeline/retry-feature.sh\n  12→- dev-pipeline/retry-bug.sh\n  13→- dev-pipeline/reset-feature.sh\n  14→- dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py\n  15→- dev-pipeline/scripts/*.py\n  16→- dev-pipeline/templates/*\n  17→\n  18→STATE_PATHS:\n  19→- dev-pipeline/state/\n  20→- dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/\n  21→\n  22→DAEMON_LOG_POLICY:\n  23→- feature daemon log -> dev-pipeline/state/pipeline-daemon.log\n  24→- bugfix daemon log -> dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/pipeline-daemon.log\n  25→\n  26→TRAPS:\n  27→- several large operational scripts (>500 lines) require cautious edits\n  28→- TODO density is concentrated in this module\n  29→\n  30→SUBDIRS:\n  31→- dev-pipeline/scripts -> .prizm-docs/pipeline/scripts.prizm\n  32→\n  33→DECISIONS:\n  34→- 2026-03-09 | pipeline-doc-init | treat shell+python pipeline as independent module\n  35→- 2026-03-10 | f001-path-policy-shared | centralize feature/bug/session/session-status/daemon-log paths via scripts/path_policy.py and JS mirror module\n  36→- 2026-03-10 | f001-us3-scope | include logs/reset in runner+service API surface using daemon wrappers and clean reset commands\n  37→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6577e9eae8544138813e12684b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:35:32.933Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"11917358-3ffa-4a03-a0b5-6aab287c5f3e","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde65af674e46c02d133d7c45cfd6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n   2→MODULE: runtime\n   3→PATH: src/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/config.js\n  11→- src/http/server.js\n  12→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n  13→- src/services/chat-service.js\n  14→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  15→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n  16→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n  17→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n  18→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n  19→- src/bot/telegram.js\n  20→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n  21→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n  22→\n  23→SUBDIRS:\n  24→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n  25→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n  26→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n  27→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n  28→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n  29→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n  30→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n  31→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n  32→\n  33→INTERFACES:\n  34→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n  35→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, text message relay\n  36→\n  37→TRAPS:\n  38→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n  39→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n  40→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n  41→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n  42→\n  43→DECISIONS:\n  44→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n  45→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n  46→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n  47→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n  48→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6577e9eae8544138813e12684b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:35:32.934Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"3b967738-4e3b-41fb-b6d2-7fff7e82fc4e","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde65b11ef354167a38c6dbbe4ce6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Feature Registry\n   2→\n   3→| ID | Slug | Title | Status | Last Updated |\n   4→|----|------|-------|--------|--------------|\n   5→| F-001 | 001-project-infrastructure-setup | Project Infrastructure Setup | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   6→| F-002 | 002-telegram-pipeline-command-router | Telegram Pipeline Command Router | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   7→| F-003 | 003-feature-and-bug-plan-ingestion | Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   8→\n   9→## F-001: Project Infrastructure Setup\n  10→\n  11→**Status:** completed  \n  12→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  13→\n  14→### Deliverables\n  15→\n  16→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Unified config loading with ENV/CLI override\n  17→- `src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js` - Feature/bug/session path resolution\n  18→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Error code definitions and factories\n  19→- `src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js` - Script execution wrapper\n  20→- `src/pipeline-infra/index.js` - Module entry point\n  21→- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - High-level pipeline control API\n  22→- `dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py` - Python path policy mirror\n  23→- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/` and `tests/services/`\n  24→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f001-user-stories.integration.test.js`\n  25→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm` and `.prizm-docs/pipeline/scripts.prizm`\n  26→\n  27→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  28→\n  29→- US-1: Unified config loading with readable validation errors\n  30→- US-2: Standard directory structure with Python/JS parity\n  31→- US-3: Unified script execution API (run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset)\n  32→- US-4: TypeScript and ESLint baseline established\n  33→\n  34→### Verification\n  35→\n  36→- `npm run typecheck`: 0 errors\n  37→- `npm run lint`: 0 warnings\n  38→- `npm test`: 29 tests pass\n  39→\n  40→---\n  41→\n  42→## F-002: Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n  43→\n  44→**Status:** completed  \n  45→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  46→\n  47→### Deliverables\n  48→\n  49→- `src/bot/commands/index.js` - Router entry point (auth, parse, validate, dispatch)\n  50→- `src/bot/commands/parser.js` - Command parsing with alias support\n  51→- `src/bot/commands/registry.js` - Dynamic command registration\n  52→- `src/bot/commands/validator.js` - Parameter validation\n  53→- `src/bot/commands/formatter.js` - User-friendly error messages\n  54→- `src/bot/commands/help.js` - Dynamic help text generation\n  55→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Pipeline command handler\n  56→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` - Bugfix shortcut handler\n  57→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js` - Planner pipeline handler\n  58→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Status query handler\n  59→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Logs query handler\n  60→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Stop pipeline handler\n  61→- Unit tests in `tests/bot/commands/`\n  62→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f002-command-router.integration.test.js`\n  63→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm`\n  64→\n  65→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  66→\n  67→- US-1: Pipeline command with run/status/logs/stop subcommands\n  68→- US-2: Bugfix command as shortcut to `/pipeline run --type=bugfix`\n  69→- US-3: Status query showing all running pipelines\n  70→- US-4: Logs query with file fallback for large output\n  71→- US-5: Stop pipeline with confirmation\n  72→- US-6: Error guidance with clear suggestions\n  73→- US-7: Authorization guard on all commands\n  74→\n  75→### Commands Implemented\n  76→\n  77→| Command | Aliases | Description |\n  78→|---------|---------|-------------|\n  79→| `/pipeline` | `/p` | Manage