{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312033559f90d806e99da4671","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"id":"20260312033559f90d806e99da4671","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde66284da54d7462cc99ba72874e","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/004-pipeline-process-controller/spec.md","content":"# Feature Specification: F-004 Pipeline Process Controller\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Feature ID | F-004 |\n| Feature Title | Pipeline Process Controller |\n| Feature Slug | 004-pipeline-process-controller |\n| Status | Planning |\n| Dependencies | F-001 (completed), F-002 (completed), F-003 (completed) |\n| Created | 2026-03-12 |\n\n## Problem Statement\n\n当前 `pipeline-control-service.js` 只是 `script-runner.js` 的薄封装层，缺乏以下关键能力：\n\n1. **并发控制缺失**：多个 Telegram 命令可能同时启动同一 pipeline，导致状态混乱\n2. **守护进程管理分散**：daemon 逻辑在 shell 脚本中，JavaScript 层无法直接查询 PID 和运行状态\n3. **单特性执行抽象不足**：`run.sh` 支持 `run_one` 但 JS 层未暴露清晰的 run-single API\n4. **错误恢复机制缺失**：超时、脚本缺失、非零退出码未映射为可操作的结构化结果\n5. **Telegram handler 紧耦合终端**：当前 handler 直接调用可能阻塞的脚本，无法优雅处理后台任务\n\n目标：将\"终端操作脚本\"能力抽象为\"程序可调用控制接口\"，提供稳定 API 给 Telegram 命令路由。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Process Controller 核心模块**\n   - 统一 feature/bugfix pipeline 控制接口\n   - 并发锁机制（mutex per pipeline type）\n   - 进程状态跟踪（running/stopped/error）\n   - PID 管理和存活检测\n\n2. **Daemon Mode 支持**\n   - 后台启动 pipeline\n   - 查询 PID、运行状态、最近执行结果\n   - 优雅停止（SIGTERM + 超时回退 SIGKILL）\n   - 重启能力\n\n3. **控制动作 API**\n   - `start(params)` - 启动 pipeline（前台或后台）\n   - `stop(params)` - 停止运行中的 pipeline\n   - `retry(params)` - 重试失败的 feature/bug\n   - `runSingle(params)` - 执行单个 feature/bug\n   - `status(params)` - 查询运行状态\n   - `logs(params)` - 获取日志\n\n4. **结构化错误映射**\n   - 超时 → EXEC_TIMEOUT + 建议\n   - 脚本缺失 → SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND + 恢复提示\n   - 非零退出 → EXEC_FAILED + 上下文\n   - 并发冲突 → LOCK_CONFLICT + 当前状态\n\n5. **Telegram Handler 集成**\n   - 更新现有 handler 使用新控制层\n   - 支持后台任务反馈\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. 新增 pipeline 类型（planner 等）\n2. 修改 dev-pipeline shell 脚本逻辑\n3. Web UI 界面\n4. 分布式锁（单机场景足够）\n\n## User Stories\n\n### US-1: Unified Pipeline Control Interface\n\n**作为** Telegram bot 用户\n**我想要** 通过统一命令启动 feature 或 bugfix pipeline\n**以便于** 不需要记忆不同的脚本路径和参数\n\n**验收标准:**\n- AC1: `/pipeline run --type=feature` 启动 feature pipeline\n- AC2: `/pipeline run --type=bugfix` 启动 bugfix pipeline\n- AC3: 返回结构化结果包含 `ok`, `message`, `pid`（后台模式）\n- AC4: 如果已有同类型 pipeline 运行中，返回错误并提示当前状态\n\n### US-2: Concurrent Execution Protection\n\n**作为** 系统\n**我想要** 防止同一 pipeline 类型被重复启动\n**以便于** 避免状态混乱和资源冲突\n\n**验收标准:**\n- AC1: feature pipeline 运行时，再次启动 feature 返回 `LOCK_CONFLICT` 错误\n- AC2: bugfix pipeline 和 feature pipeline 可以并行运行\n- AC3: 错误响应包含当前运行 pipeline 的 PID 和启动时间\n- AC4: 支持 `--force` 参数强制停止并重启（可选）\n\n### US-3: Daemon Mode Management\n\n**作为** Telegram bot 用户\n**我想要** 在后台启动 pipeline 并随时查询状态\n**以便于** 不阻塞 Telegram 会话，长时间运行也能监控\n\n**验收标准:**\n- AC1: `start({ daemon: true })` 后台启动并立即返回 PID\n- AC2: `status()` 返回 `running`, `pid`, `startTime`, `progress`\n- AC3: `stop()` 发送 SIGTERM，30秒超时后 SIGKILL\n- AC4: 停止后 `status()` 返回 `stopped` 和 `lastResult`\n\n### US-4: Single Feature Execution\n\n**作为** Telegram bot 用户\n**我想要** 执行单个 feature 或 bug fix\n**以便于** 针对性处理特定任务而不运行整个 pipeline\n\n**验收标准:**\n- AC1: `runSingle({ targetId: 'F-007' })` 执行单个 feature\n- AC2: `runSingle({ targetId: 'B-003', pipelineType: 'bugfix' })` 执行单个 bug fix\n- AC3: 返回执行结果和日志路径\n- AC4: 支持 `--clean` 参数清理 artifacts 后执行\n\n### US-5: Structured Error Recovery\n\n**作为** Telegram bot 用户\n**我想要** 收到结构化的错误信息和恢复建议\n**以便于** 理解问题并采取正确的后续操作\n\n**验收标准:**\n- AC1: 超时错误包含 `code: EXEC_TIMEOUT`, `message`, `hint: \"Increase timeout or check logs\"`\n- AC2: 脚本缺失错误包含 `code: SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND`, `hint: \"Run npm install or check path\"`\n- AC3: 并发冲突错误包含 `code: LOCK_CONFLICT`, `currentPid`, `hint: \"Stop first or wait for completion\"`\n- AC4: 所有错误响应包含 `recoverable: boolean` 标记\n\n### US-6: Telegram Handler Integration\n\n**作为** 开发者\n**我想要** Telegram handler 调用稳定的控制层 API\n**以便于** handler 专注于消息格式化，不处理脚本调用细节\n\n**验收标准:**\n- AC1: `handlePipeline` 调用 `processController.start()` 而非直接调用 script-runner\n- AC2: 后台任务立即返回\"已启动\"消息，不阻塞 Telegram\n- AC3: `/status` 命令使用 `processController.status()` 获取结构化数据\n- AC4: 错误消息使用统一格式化器\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n\n### NFR-1: Performance\n- `status()` 调用响应时间 < 100ms\n- PID 存活检测时间 < 10ms\n\n### NFR-2: Reliability\n- 进程状态文件使用原子写入\n- 崩溃后重启能检测并清理陈旧 PID\n\n### NFR-3: Testability\n- 控制层与脚本执行解耦，支持 mock runner\n- 单元测试覆盖率 > 80%\n- 集成测试覆盖关键用户故事\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n| Criterion | Verification Method |\n|-----------|---------------------|\n| 统一控制接口启动 feature/bugfix pipeline | Integration test + manual |\n| 并发互斥保护生效 | Unit test + integration test |\n| 结构化错误映射 | Unit test |\n| 后台模式 PID/状态查询 | Integration test |\n| Telegram handler 可用新 API | Integration test |\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| 进程状态文件损坏 | 高 | 使用 JSON 校验 + 默认值回退 |\n| PID 重用导致误判 | 中 | 结合启动时间验证 |\n| 并发锁死锁 | 高 | 使用 try-lock + 超时释放 |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Status |\n|------------|------|--------|\n| F-001 Pipeline Infrastructure | Module | Completed |\n| F-002 Telegram Command Router | Module | Completed |\n| F-003 Plan Ingestion | Module | Completed |\n| dev-pipeline/launch-daemon.sh | Script | Exists |\n| dev-pipeline/run.sh | Script | Exists |\n| dev-pipeline/run-bugfix.sh | Script | Exists |\n\n## Glossary\n\n| Term | Definition |\n|------|------------|\n| Pipeline | 特指 dev-pipeline 执行流程（feature 或 bugfix） |\n| Daemon Mode | 后台运行模式，进程与 Telegram 会话解耦 |\n| Mutex | 互斥锁，确保同一 pipeline 类型同时只有一个实例运行 |\n| PID | Process ID，进程标识符 |\n| Target ID | Feature ID (F-xxx) 或 Bug ID (B-xxx) |\n"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":50635,"output_tokens":2025,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6577e9eae8544138813e12684b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:36:34.447Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"e778f981-d741-417b-9d3e-78e7b1a8b3b6","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde66284da54d7462cc99ba72874e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully created and wrote to new file: /Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/004-pipeline-process-controller/spec.md"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6577e9eae8544138813e12684b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:36:34.462Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312033634553cb744a24c47e1","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"id":"20260312033634553cb744a24c47e1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Spec created successfully. No `[NEEDS CLARIFICATION]` markers found. Proceeding to Step 2: Run `prizmkit.plan` → generate `plan.md`."}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6577e9eae8544138813e12684b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:37:30.189Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312033634553cb744a24c47e1","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"id":"20260312033634553cb744a24c47e1","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde66b699798ea28c2594824fb3e5","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/004-pipeline-process-controller/plan.md","content":"# Technical Implementation Plan: F-004 Pipeline Process Controller\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Feature ID | F-004 |\n| Feature Slug | 004-pipeline-process-controller |\n| Version | 1.0 |\n| Created | 2026-03-12 |\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Telegram Layer                               │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │\n│  │ handlePipeline│  │ handleBugfix │  │ handleStatus │              │\n│  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘              │\n│         │                 │                  │                      │\n│         └─────────────────┼──────────────────┘                      │\n│                           ▼                                         │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n┌───────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   Process Controller Layer (NEW)                    │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │              ProcessController (Core Module)                 │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐         │   │\n│  │  │ MutexLock   │  │ StateTracker│  │ PidManager  │         │   │\n│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘         │   │\n│  │                                                              │   │\n│  │  Methods: start, stop, retry, runSingle, status, logs       │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                           │                                         │\n│  ┌────────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │              DaemonLauncher (Daemon Mode)                    │   │\n│  │  Methods: startDaemon, stopDaemon, queryDaemon              │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                           │                                         │\n│  ┌────────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │              ErrorMapper (Error Handling)                    │   │\n│  │  Maps exit codes, signals, timeouts → structured errors     │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n┌───────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Infrastructure Layer (F-001)                     │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐    │\n│  │ ScriptRunner    │  │ ConfigLoader    │  │ ErrorCodes      │    │\n│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n┌───────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Shell Scripts (dev-pipeline/)                    │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐    │\n│  │ launch-daemon.sh│  │ run.sh /        │  │ retry-*.sh      │    │\n│  │                 │  │ run-bugfix.sh   │  │ reset-*.sh      │    │\n│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Component Design\n\n### 1. ProcessController (Core Module)\n\n**Location:** `src/services/process-controller.js`\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Unified API for pipeline control actions\n- Concurrency lock management\n- State tracking and persistence\n- Coordination of daemon operations\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js` (executePipelineCommand)\n- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` (loadPipelineInfraConfig)\n- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` (INFRA_ERROR_CODES)\n- `./daemon-launcher.js` (DaemonLauncher)\n- `./error-mapper.js` (ErrorMapper)\n\n### 2. DaemonLauncher\n\n**Location:** `src/services/daemon-launcher.js`\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Execute launch-daemon.sh with proper arguments\n- Parse JSON output from daemon scripts\n- Manage daemon lifecycle (start/stop/status/logs)\n- Handle PID file operations\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js`\n- `fs` (for PID file verification)\n\n### 3. ErrorMapper\n\n**Location:** `src/services/error-mapper.js`\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Map exit codes to structured errors\n- Generate recovery hints\n- Provide actionable error messages\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`\n\n### 4. StateTracker\n\n**Location:** `src/services/state-tracker.js`\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Read/write pipeline state files\n- Track running pipeline metadata\n- Provide status aggregation\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `fs`, `path`\n- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js`\n\n### 5. MutexLock\n\n**Location:** `src/services/mutex-lock.js`\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- In-memory lock management per pipeline type\n- Lock acquisition with timeout\n- Automatic stale lock cleanup\n\n**Dependencies:** None (pure in-memory)\n\n## Interface Design\n\n### ProcessController API\n\n```typescript\n// Type definitions for documentation\ninterface PipelineParams {\n  pipelineType?: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  targetId?: string;\n  listPath?: string;\n  daemon?: boolean;\n  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n  timeoutMs?: number;\n  force?: boolean;\n  clean?: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface ProcessResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  exitCode: number;\n  status: 'success' | 'failed' | 'running' | 'stopped' | 'timed_out';\n  message?: string;\n  pid?: number;\n  startTime?: string;\n  logs?: string;\n  progress?: ProgressInfo;\n  error?: StructuredError;\n}\n\ninterface StructuredError {\n  code: string;\n  message: string;\n  hint?: string;\n  context?: Record<string, any>;\n  recoverable: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface ProgressInfo {\n  total: number;\n  completed: number;\n  inProgress: number;\n  failed: number;\n  pending: number;\n  percent: number;\n}\n\ninterface ProcessController {\n  // Start pipeline (all features/bugs)\n  start(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n  \n  // Stop running pipeline\n  stop(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n  \n  // Retry failed target\n  retry(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n  \n  // Run single feature/bug\n  runSingle(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n  \n  // Get status\n  status(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n  \n  // Get logs\n  logs(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n}\n```\n\n### DaemonLauncher API\n\n```typescript\ninterface DaemonLauncher {\n  start(params: {\n    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n    listPath?: string;\n    envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n  }): Promise<{ ok: boolean; pid: number; logFile: string }>;\n  \n  stop(params: {\n    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  }): Promise<{ ok: boolean; message: string }>;\n  \n  status(params: {\n    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  }): Promise<{\n    running: boolean;\n    pid?: number;\n    startTime?: string;\n    logFile?: string;\n    progress?: ProgressInfo;\n  }>;\n  \n  logs(params: {\n    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n    lines?: number;\n  }): Promise<string>;\n}\n```\n\n### ErrorMapper API\n\n```typescript\ninterface ErrorMapper {\n  mapResult(raw: {\n    exitCode?: number;\n    signal?: string;\n    timedOut?: boolean;\n    stderr?: string;\n  }): StructuredError | null;\n  \n  getLockError(currentPid: number, startTime: string): StructuredError;\n  \n  getScriptNotFoundError(scriptPath: string): StructuredError;\n  \n  getTimeoutError(timeoutMs: number): StructuredError;\n}\n```\n\n## Data Model\n\n### Pipeline State File\n\n**Path:** `dev-pipeline/state/.controller-state.json` (feature)\n**Path:** `dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/.controller-state.json` (bugfix)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"pipelineType\": \"feature\",\n  \"status\": \"running\",\n  \"pid\": 12345,\n  \"startedAt\": \"2026-03-12T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"featureList\": \"/path/to/feature-list.json\",\n  \"daemonMode\": true,\n  \"envOverrides\": {\n    \"MAX_RETRIES\": \"5\"\n  },\n  \"lastResult\": {\n    \"ok\": false,\n    \"exitCode\": 1,\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-03-12T09:15:00Z\",\n    \"message\": \"Pipeline stopped by user\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Lock State (In-Memory)\n\n```javascript\nconst locks = {\n  feature: {\n    locked: false,\n    pid: null,\n    acquiredAt: null\n  },\n  bugfix: {\n    locked: false,\n    pid: null,\n    acquiredAt: null\n  }\n};\n```\n\n## User Story Mapping\n\n| User Story | Primary Component | Secondary Components |\n|------------|-------------------|----------------------|\n| US-1: Unified Control | ProcessController.start() | DaemonLauncher, ErrorMapper |\n| US-2: Concurrent Protection | MutexLock | ProcessController, ErrorMapper |\n| US-3: Daemon Mode | DaemonLauncher | ProcessController, StateTracker |\n| US-4: Single Execution | ProcessController.runSingle() | ScriptRunner |\n| US-5: Error Recovery | ErrorMapper | ProcessController |\n| US-6: Handler Integration | ProcessController | Telegram handlers |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Module | Test File | Coverage Target |\n|--------|-----------|-----------------|\n| ProcessController | `tests/services/process-controller.test.js` | 85% |\n| DaemonLauncher | `tests/services/daemon-launcher.test.js` | 80% |\n| ErrorMapper | `tests/services/error-mapper.test.js` | 90% |\n| MutexLock | `tests/services/mutex-lock.test.js` | 90% |\n| StateTracker | `tests/services/state-tracker.test.js` | 85% |\n\n**Key Test Scenarios:**\n- Lock acquisition and release\n- Concurrent start rejection\n- Exit code mapping\n- Timeout handling\n- PID file parsing\n- State persistence\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File:** `tests/integration/f004-process-controller.integration.test.js`\n\n| Scenario | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| I-001 | Start/stop feature pipeline daemon |\n| I-002 | Start/stop bugfix pipeline daemon |\n| I-003 | Concurrent start rejected with error |\n| I-004 | Run single feature with clean |\n| I-005 | Status query returns progress |\n| I-006 | Error recovery with hints |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n- Mock script-runner for unit tests\n- Test state files in `tests/fixtures/state/`\n- Sample feature-list.json and bug-fix-list.json\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── services/\n│   ├── process-controller.js      # Core controller (NEW)\n│   ├── daemon-launcher.js         # Daemon wrapper (NEW)\n│   ├── error-mapper.js            # Error mapping (NEW)\n│   ├── state-tracker.js           # State management (NEW)\n│   ├── mutex-lock.js              # Concurrency lock (NEW)\n│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js # Update to use ProcessController\n│   └── plan-ingestion-service.js  # Unchanged\n├── bot/commands/handlers/\n│   ├── pipeline.js                # Update to use new API\n│   ├── bugfix.js                  # Update to use new API\n│   ├── status.js                  # Update to use new API\n│   └── stop.js                    # Update to use new API\n└── pipeline-infra/\n    └── (unchanged from F-001)\n\ntests/\n├── services/\n│   ├── process-controller.test.js\n│   ├── daemon-launcher.test.js\n│   ├── error-mapper.test.js\n│   ├── state-tracker.test.js\n│   └── mutex-lock.test.js\n├── integration/\n│   └── f004-process-controller.integration.test.js\n└── fixtures/\n    └── state/\n        ├── feature-state.json\n        └── bugfix-state.json\n```\n\n## Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (T-010 ~ T-029)\n- MutexLock implementation\n- ErrorMapper implementation\n- StateTracker implementation\n\n### Phase 2: Core Controller (T-030 ~ T-059)\n- ProcessController core logic\n- DaemonLauncher integration\n- API surface implementation\n\n### Phase 3: Integration (T-060 ~ T-089)\n- Update pipeline-control-service\n- Update Telegram handlers\n- Integration testing\n\n### Phase 4: Polish (T-090 ~ T-099)\n- Documentation updates\n- Edge case handling\n- Performance optimization\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| PID reuse causes false positive | Low | High | Include start time in validation |\n| Lock deadlock on crash | Medium | High | Implement lock timeout (60s) + cleanup on status check |\n| State file corruption | Low | High | Use atomic write + validation + default fallback |\n| Script output format change | Low | Medium | Parse defensively with try-catch + fallback |\n| Memory leak in long-running process | Low | Medium | No persistent state in memory, use files |\n\n## Dependencies Alignment\n\n### From F-001 (Infrastructure)\n- `script-runner.js` - Used by DaemonLauncher\n- `config-loader.js` - Configuration loading\n- `error-codes.js` - Error code definitions\n- `path-policy.js` - Path resolution\n\n### From F-002 (Command Router)\n- Handler structure preserved\n- Command metadata extended\n- Formatter utilities reused\n\n### From F-003 (Plan Ingestion)\n- `resolvePlanListPath()` used for list path resolution\n- Plan version management integrated\n\n## Decisions Log\n\n| Date | Decision | Rationale |\n|------|----------|-----------|\n| 2026-03-12 | Use in-memory mutex over file-based lock | Single-machine deployment, simpler implementation |\n| 2026-03-12 | Keep daemon scripts unchanged | Existing scripts work well, wrap in JS layer |\n| 2026-03-12 | State files in dev-pipeline/state | Consistent with existing pipeline state location |\n| 2026-03-12 | ProcessController as separate module from pipeline-control-service | Clean separation, backward compatibility |\n"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":52743,"output_tokens":3539,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6577e9eae8544138813e12684b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:37:30.196Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
