 `tests/services/state-tracker.test.js`\n  - `tests/services/mutex-lock.test.js`\n  - `tests/integration/f004-process-controller.integration.test.js`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- All test files exist with `describe` blocks\n- Tests use Jest conventions\n- `npm test` runs without errors (tests may be empty)\n\n**Complexity:** Low\n\n---\n\n### T-003: Create Test Fixtures\n\n- [ ] [T-003] [P] Create test fixtures — file: tests/fixtures/state/feature-state.json\n\n**Goal:** Create sample state files for testing.\n\n**Input:**\n- plan.md data model section\n- Existing pipeline state files\n\n**Output:**\n- `tests/fixtures/state/feature-state.json`\n- `tests/fixtures/state/bugfix-state.json`\n- `tests/fixtures/feature-list.json`\n- `tests/fixtures/bug-fix-list.json`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Files follow data model schema\n- Files contain realistic sample data\n\n**Complexity:** Low\n\n---\n\n## Phase: Foundational (T-010 ~ T-059)\n\n### T-010: Implement MutexLock\n\n- [ ] [T-010] [P] Implement MutexLock module — file: src/services/mutex-lock.js\n\n**Goal:** Create in-memory lock mechanism for pipeline types.\n\n**Input:**\n- plan.md MutexLock API design\n- Pipeline types: 'feature', 'bugfix'\n\n**Output:**\n- `createMutexLock()` factory function\n- Methods: `acquire(type, pid)`, `release(type)`, `isLocked(type)`, `getLockInfo(type)`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- `acquire()` returns `true` if lock acquired, `false` if already locked\n- `release()` clears the lock\n- Lock includes `pid` and `acquiredAt` timestamp\n- Unit tests pass with >90% coverage\n\n**Complexity:** Medium\n\n---\n\n### T-011: Write MutexLock Tests\n\n- [ ] [T-011] [P] Write MutexLock unit tests — file: tests/services/mutex-lock.test.js\n\n**Goal:** Comprehensive tests for MutexLock.\n\n**Input:**\n- T-010 MutexLock implementation\n\n**Output:**\n- Test cases for:\n  - Basic acquire/release cycle\n  - Double acquire rejected\n  - Release by different caller (no-op)\n  - Lock info retrieval\n  - Concurrent access simulation\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- All test cases pass\n- Coverage > 90%\n\n**Complexity:** Medium\n\n---\n\n### T-012: Implement ErrorMapper\n\n- [ ] [T-012] [P] Implement ErrorMapper module — file: src/services/error-mapper.js\n\n**Goal:** Map exit codes and signals to structured errors.\n\n**Input:**\n- plan.md ErrorMapper API design\n- `INFRA_ERROR_CODES` from error-codes.js\n\n**Output:**\n- `createErrorMapper()` factory\n- Methods: `mapResult()`, `getLockError()`, `getScriptNotFoundError()`, `getTimeoutError()`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Exit code 0 → no error\n- Exit code 124 → EXEC_TIMEOUT error\n- Non-zero exit → EXEC_FAILED error\n- Signal → EXEC_FAILED with signal info\n- All errors include `recoverable` flag and `hint`\n\n**Complexity:** Medium\n\n---\n\n### T-013: Write ErrorMapper Tests\n\n- [ ] [T-013] [P] Write ErrorMapper unit tests — file: tests/services/error-mapper.test.js\n\n**Goal:** Comprehensive tests for ErrorMapper.\n\n**Input:**\n- T-012 ErrorMapper implementation\n\n**Output:**\n- Test cases for all exit code mappings\n- Test cases for signal handling\n- Test cases for lock error generation\n- Test cases for hint generation\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- All test cases pass\n- Coverage > 90%\n\n**Complexity:** Medium\n\n---\n\n### T-014: Implement StateTracker\n\n- [ ] [T-014] [P] Implement StateTracker module — file: src/services/state-tracker.js\n\n**Goal:** Manage pipeline state file operations.\n\n**Input:**\n- plan.md data model section\n- State file paths from config\n\n**Output:**\n- `createStateTracker()` factory\n- Methods: `readState(pipelineType)`, `writeState(pipelineType, data)`, `clearState(pipelineType)`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Reads state from correct paths\n- Writes state atomically (write to temp, then rename)\n- Returns default state if file missing\n- Handles JSON parse errors gracefully\n\n**Complexity:** Medium\n\n---\n\n### T-015: Write StateTracker Tests\n\n- [ ] [T-015] [P] Wri