{"type":"user","uuid":"bd837db6-8b5e-44b6-94af-f99ee8b8f10b","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde68fdbbf5f7969c730b3167e749","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-reviewer\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated quality reviewer. Uses prizmkit.analyze for cross-document consistency, prizmkit.code-review for spec compliance and code quality, and writes integration tests. Use when performing analysis, testing, or code review.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-code-review, prizmkit-analyze, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Reviewer Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的质量审查员。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"质检员 + 校对员\"——不生产产品但确保质量，负责两个阶段的工作：\n  14→1. **交叉校验（Phase 4）**: 在实现前用 `prizmkit.analyze` 检查 spec/plan/tasks 的一致性\n  15→2. **评审（Phase 6）**: 在实现后用 `prizmkit.code-review` 检查代码质量，编写和执行集成测试\n  16→\n  17→### 项目上下文\n  18→\n  19→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。审查前先读 `root.prizm` 了解项目规则（RULES）、模式（PATTERNS）和已知陷阱（TRAPS），需要时读取模块级文档。\n  20→\n  21→### 制品路径\n  22→\n  23→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  24→|------|------|\n  25→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  26→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  27→\n  28→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  29→\n  30→1. Phase 4 时运行 `prizmkit.analyze` 做交叉一致性校验\n  31→2. Phase 6 时运行 `prizmkit.code-review` 做规格合规和代码质量审查\n  32→3. Phase 6 时编写和执行集成测试，验证模块间交互\n  33→4. 验证实际实现是否符合 plan.md 中的接口设计\n  34→5. 验证跨模块数据流的完整性和正确性\n  35→6. 测试边界条件和异常路径\n  36→7. 检查代码是否符合 `.prizm-docs/` RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  37→8. 审查是**只读操作**（Phase 4 和 Phase 6 的审查部分不修改代码文件）\n  38→9. 集成测试用例必须覆盖 spec.md 定义的所有用户故事\n  39→\n  40→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  41→\n  42→- 不编写实现代码（Dev 的职责）\n  43→- 不分解任务（PM 的职责）\n  44→- 不进行任务调度（Coordinator 的职责）\n  45→\n  46→### 行为规则\n  47→\n  48→```\n  49→REV-01: Phase 4 使用 prizmkit.analyze 做交叉校验\n  50→REV-02: Phase 6 使用 prizmkit.code-review 做代码审查\n  51→REV-03: 每个发现必须引用具体的文件路径和行号\n  52→REV-04: CRITICAL 级别发现必须包含具体的修复建议\n  53→REV-05: 最多 30 个发现（保持可操作性）\n  54→REV-06: Spec compliance 失败始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  55→REV-07: 安全发现始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  56→REV-08: 集成测试必须覆盖 spec.md 所有用户故事\n  57→REV-09: 审查代码是否符合 .prizm-docs/ PATTERNS 和 RULES\n  58→```\n  59→\n  60→### Phase 4 工作流程：交叉校验\n  61→\n  62→**前置条件**: PM 已完成 spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md\n  63→\n  64→1. 运行 `prizmkit.analyze`（只读）\n  65→   - 输入: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n  66→   - 6 个检测通道: 重复检测、歧义检测、不完整检测、Prizm 规则对齐、覆盖缺口、不一致性\n  67→   - 输出: 一致性分析报告（仅对话输出）\n  68→2. 如发现 CRITICAL 问题，报告给 Coordinator 退回 PM 修复\n  69→3. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含分析结果）\n  70→\n  71→### Phase 6 工作流程：评审\n  72→\n  73→**前置条件**: Dev 已完成实现，所有任务标记 `[x]`\n  74→\n  75→1. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm`，重点关注 RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  76→2. 运行 `prizmkit.code-review`（只读）\n  77→   - 6 个审查维度: 规格符合度、计划遵循度、代码质量、安全性、一致性、测试覆盖\n  78→   - 判定: PASS | PASS WITH WARNINGS | NEEDS FIXES\n  79→3. 编写和执行集成测试:\n  80→   - 接口合规性（请求格式、响应格式）\n  81→   - 跨模块数据流完整性\n  82→   - 用户故事验收标准（来自 spec.md）\n  83→   - 边界条件和异常路径\n  84→4. 生成统一评审报告\n  85→5. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）\n  86→\n  87→### 判定标准\n  88→\n  89→| 判定 | 条件 | 后续动作 |\n  90→|------|------|---------|\n  91→| **PASS** | 无 CRITICAL 或 HIGH 发现 | 进入下一阶段 |\n  92→| **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS** | 无 CRITICAL，有 HIGH 发现 | 记录待改进项，可进入下一阶段 |\n  93→| **NEEDS_FIXES** | 存在 CRITICAL 发现 | 退回 Dev 修复后重新评审 |\n  94→\n  95→### 严重级别\n  96→\n  97→| 级别 | 定义 | 示例 |\n  98→|------|------|------|\n  99→| CRITICAL | 安全风险或严重架构问题 | SQL 注入、硬编码密钥 |\n 100→| HIGH | 影响可维护性的显著问题 | 规格不符、大量重复代码 |\n 101→| MEDIUM | 代码质量改进点 | 命名不统一、缺少注释 |\n 102→| LOW | 风格建议 | 格式微调、可选优化 |\n 103→\n 104→### 异常处理\n 105→\n 106→| 场景 | 策略 |\n 107→|------|------|\n 108→| analyze 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 PM 修复 |\n 109→| code-review 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 Dev 修复 |\n 110→| 集成测试失败 | 分类严重级别 → ISSUE_REPORT → Coordinator 派发给 Dev |\n 111→| 审查发现超过 30 个 | 只保留最严重的 30 个 |\n 112→| Prizm RULES 违规 | 自动标记为 CRITICAL |\n 113→\n 114→### 通信规则\n 115→\n 116→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n 117→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）标志完成\n 118→- 发送 ISSUE_REPORT 报告 CRITICAL 发现\n 119→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 120→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde68e81fd6885d5a22f36ce71dc2","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:39:10.937Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"23b0c49b-a8cd-4da4-ad63-3a79edcc888a","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde68ffdcdfb51d4c0ef3ffdecf26","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-004: Pipeline Process Controller\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→构建 pipeline 进程控制层，统一封装 dev-pipeline/run.sh 与 run-bugfix.sh 的启动、停止、重试、单特性执行与后台守护模式。该层提供稳定 API 给 Telegram 命令路由调用，并负责并发锁、超时、退出码映射与异常恢复。目标是把当前\"终端操作脚本\"能力抽象为\"程序可调用控制接口\"。\n   6→\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→## User Stories\n  10→\n  11→### US-1: Unified Pipeline Start\n  12→\n  13→**As a** Telegram 用户或系统集成者  \n  14→**I want** 通过统一的控制接口启动 feature pipeline 或 bugfix pipeline  \n  15→**So that** 我不需要关心底层脚本的差异，且能获得标准化的执行结果\n  16→\n  17→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  18→- AC-1.1: `startPipeline({ type: 'feature' | 'bugfix', targetId?, listPath?, daemon?: boolean })` 可启动指定类型管道\n  19→- AC-1.2: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, runId, pid?, message, errorCode? }`\n  20→- AC-1.3: 若指定 `daemon: true`，以后台守护模式启动，返回 PID\n  21→- AC-1.4: 若管道已在运行中（并发锁检查失败），返回 `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED` 错误\n  22→\n  23→---\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: Pipeline Stop\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 运维人员  \n  28→**I want** 通过控制接口停止正在运行的管道  \n  29→**So that** 我可以从 Telegram 或 API 中止异常的管道执行\n  30→\n  31→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  32→- AC-2.1: `stopPipeline({ type: 'feature' | 'bugfix' })` 可停止指定类型的守护进程\n  33→- AC-2.2: 若进程已停止，返回 `ALREADY_STOPPED` 状态而非错误\n  34→- AC-2.3: 停止操作有 10 秒超时，超时后强制终止\n  35→- AC-2.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, previousPid, message }`\n  36→\n  37→---\n  38→\n  39→### US-3: Target Retry\n  40→\n  41→**As a** 开发者  \n  42→**I want** 重试某个失败的 feature 或 bugfix 目标  \n  43→**So that** 我可以针对单个失败项进行修复而不影响其他已完成的工作\n  44→\n  45→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  46→- AC-3.1: `retryTarget({ type, targetId, listPath? })` 可重试指定目标\n  47→- AC-3.2: 若目标不存在或状态不允许可重试，返回明确错误\n  48→- AC-3.3: 支持前台和后台模式\n  49→- AC-3.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, targetId, message }`\n  50→\n  51→---\n  52→\n  53→### US-4: Run Single Feature\n  54→\n  55→**As a** 开发者  \n  56→**I want** 单独运行某个特定的 feature 或 bugfix  \n  57→**So that** 我可以测试或调试单个工作项而不运行整个队列\n  58→\n  59→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  60→- AC-4.1: `runSingle({ type, targetId, listPath? })` 可执行单个目标\n  61→- AC-4.2: 执行完成后返回完整的执行结果（含 stdout/stderr）\n  62→- AC-4.3: 支持超时配置\n  63→- AC-4.4: 不影响管道整体状态（独立执行）\n  64→\n  65→---\n  66→\n  67→### US-5: Status Query\n  68→\n  69→**As a** 运维人员  \n  70→**I want** 查询管道的当前状态  \n  71→**So that** 我可以了解系统运行情况并做出决策\n  72→\n  73→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  74→- AC-5.1: `getPipelineStatus({ type })` 返回管道状态对象\n  75→- AC-5.2: 状态对象包含 `{ isRunning, pid?, currentFeature?, startedAt?, lastResult? }`\n  76→- AC-5.3: 若有运行中的目标，包含 `currentFeature` 和 `startedAt`\n  77→- AC-5.4: 若无运行中管道，返回 `lastResult`（最近一次执行结果）\n  78→\n  79→---\n  80→\n  81→### US-6: Logs Query\n  82→\n  83→**As a** 运维人员  \n  84→**I want** 获取管道执行日志  \n  85→**So that** 我可以诊断问题或监控执行进度\n  86→\n  87→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  88→- AC-6.1: `getPipelineLogs({ type, lines?: number })` 返回日志内容\n  89→- AC-6.2: 默认返回最近 100 行，可通过 `lines` 参数调整\n  90→- AC-6.3: 日志不存在时返回空字符串而非错误\n  91→- AC-6.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, logs, logPath }`\n  92→\n  93→---\n  94→\n  95→### US-7: Concurrency Protection\n  96→\n  97→**As a** 系统管理员  \n  98→**I want** 防止多个管道实例同时运行  \n  99→**So that** 系统资源不被过度占用且状态文件不会冲突\n 100→\n 101→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 102→- AC-7.1: 同类型管道同一时间只能有一个实例运行\n 103→- AC-7.2: 锁获取失败时返回 `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED` 错误，含当前持有者信息\n 104→- AC-7.3: 锁在进程异常退出时自动释放（通过 PID 检测）\n 105→- AC-7.4: 提供 `forceUnlock({ type })` 用于强制释放锁（管理员操作）\n 106→\n 107→---\n 108→\n 109→### US-8: Error Mapping\n 110→\n 111→**As a** Telegram handler 开发者  \n 112→**I want** 所有错误都有结构化的错误码和消息  \n 113→**So that** 我可以向用户展示友好的错误提示而非原始错误堆栈\n 114→\n 115→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 116→- AC-8.1: 所有错误返回 `{ ok: false, errorCode: string, message: string, hint?: string }`\n 117→- AC-8.2: 错误码覆盖: `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED`, `SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND`, `EXEC_TIMEOUT`, `EXEC_FAILED`, `INVALID_TARGET`, `PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING`, `ALREADY_STOPPED`\n 118→- AC-8.3: 超时错误包含超时时长信息\n 119→- AC-8.4: 脚本缺失错误包含脚本路径\n 120→\n 121→---\n 122→\n 123→### US-9: Telegram Handler Integration\n 124→\n 125→**As a** Telegram bot 开发者  \n 126→**I want** 控制层接口可直接被 Telegram handler 调用  \n 127→**So that** 命令路由实现变得简单且不依赖终端交互\n 128→\n 129→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 130→- AC-9.1: 所有方法返回 Promise，可被 async/await 调用\n 131→- AC-9.2: 无需传递 process.stdin/stdout 依赖\n 132→- AC-9.3: 执行结果可通过 JSON 序列化传输\n 133→- AC-9.4: 提供 `createPipelineController()` 工厂函数，支持依赖注入\n 134→\n 135→---\n 136→\n 137→## Non-Functional Requirements\n 138→\n 139→### NFR-1: Performance\n 140→- 控制接口响应时间 < 100ms（不含脚本执行时间）\n 141→- 状态查询 < 50ms\n 142→- 日志读取（100 行）< 200ms\n 143→\n 144→### NFR-2: Reliability\n 145→- 锁机制可靠性 > 99.9%（无死锁场景）\n 146→- 进程异常退出时资源清理率 100%\n 147→\n 148→### NFR-3: Maintainability\n 149→- 核心模块单文件，函数长度 < 100 行\n 150→- 错误码定义在单一文件中管理\n 151→- 测试覆盖率 > 90%\n 152→\n 153→### NFR-4: Extensibility\n 154→- 支持未来添加新的 pipeline 类型（如 `planner`）\n 155→- 错误码可扩展\n 156→- 状态模型可扩展\n 157→\n 158→---\n 159→\n 160→## Scope Boundaries\n 161→\n 162→### In Scope\n 163→- Pipeline 控制器核心模块 (`src/services/pipeline-controller.js`)\n 164→- 并发锁管理器 (`src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js`)\n 165→- 状态管理器 (`src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js`)\n 166→- 错误码扩展 (`src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`)\n 167→- 与现有 daemon 脚本的集成\n 168→- 单元测试与集成测试\n 169→\n 170→### Out of Scope\n 171→- Telegram 命令路由实现（已在 F-002 完成）\n 172→- Pipeline 内部逻辑修改\n 173→- Web UI\n 174→- 数据库持久化（继续使用 JSON 文件）\n 175→- 认证授权（由上层路由处理）\n 176→\n 177→---\n 178→\n 179→## Dependencies\n 180→\n 181→| Dependency | Type | Status | Notes |\n 182→|------------|------|--------|-------|\n 183→| F-001 | Feature | completed | 提供基础架构 (script-runner, error-codes, path-policy) |\n 184→| F-002 | Feature | completed | 提供命令路由层 (将调用 F-004 API) |\n 185→| launch-daemon.sh | Script | existing | Feature daemon 管理脚本 |\n 186→| launch-bugfix-daemon.sh | Script | existing | Bugfix daemon 管理脚本 |\n 187→| retry-feature.sh | Script | existing | Feature 重试脚本 |\n 188→| retry-bug.sh | Script | existing | Bugfix 重试脚本 |\n 189→\n 190→---\n 191→\n 192→## Risks\n 193→\n 194→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 195→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 196→| 并发锁实现复杂导致死锁 | Medium | High | 使用简单的文件锁 + PID 检测，避免复杂同步原语 |\n 197→| Daemon 脚本输出格式变化 | Low | Medium | 建立脚本输出契约，添加输出解析测试 |\n 198→| 大日志文件读取阻塞 | Low | Medium | 使用流式读取或限制读取行数 |\n 199→| 跨平台兼容性（macOS/Linux） | Low | Low | 主要使用 Node.js API，脚本在 WSL/Git Bash 兼容 |\n 200→\n 201→---\n 202→\n 203→## Technical Notes\n 204→\n 205→### 现有基础设施\n 206→- `script-runner.js` 已提供基本的命令执行和错误映射\n 207→- `pipeline-control-service.js` 已提供基础 API，但缺少并发保护和 daemon 模式\n 208→- `launch-daemon.sh` 和 `launch-bugfix-daemon.sh` 提供 PID 管理和日志合并\n 209→\n 210→### 设计方向\n 211→- 扩展 `pipeline-control-service.js` 或创建新模块 `pipeline-controller.js`\n 212→- 锁管理器使用文件锁 (`flock` 或 `.lock` 文件 + PID 校验)\n 213→- 状态管理器读取现有的 `pipeline.json` 和 `.pipeline-meta.json`\n 214→\n 215→---\n 216→\n 217→## Decisions\n 218→\n 219→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 220→|----|------|----------|\n 221→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | 使用文件锁 + PID 校验实现并发保护，避免引入外部依赖 |\n 222→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 创建独立的 `pipeline-controller.js` 模块，而非扩展现有 `pipeline-control-service.js`，以保持职责清晰 |\n 223→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 复用现有 daemon 脚本的输出格式，不做脚本修改 |\n 224→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde68e81fd6885d5a22f36ce71dc2","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:39:10.938Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"2adb6825-4762-45fc-8fde-b4d503029c6c","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde69022f0b804cd41a2c4a433947","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Technical Implementation Plan: F-004 Pipeline Process Controller\n   2→\n   3→| Field | Value |\n   4→|-------|-------|\n   5→| Feature ID | F-004 |\n   6→| Feature Slug | 004-pipeline-process-controller |\n   7→| Version | 1.0 |\n   8→| Created | 2026-03-12 |\n   9→\n  10→## Architecture Overview\n  11→\n  12→```\n  13→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  14→│                        Telegram Layer                               │\n  15→│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │\n  16→│  │ handlePipeline│  │ handleBugfix │  │ handleStatus │              │\n  17→│  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘              │\n  18→│         │                 │                  │                      │\n  19→│         └─────────────────┼──────────────────┘                      │\n  20→│                           ▼                                         │\n  21→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  22→                            │\n  23→┌───────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  24→│                   Process Controller Layer (NEW)                    │\n  25→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  26→│  │              ProcessController (Core Module)                 │   │\n  27→│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐         │   │\n  28→│  │  │ MutexLock   │  │ StateTracker│  │ PidManager  │         │   │\n  29→│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘         │   │\n  30→│  │                                                              │   │\n  31→│  │  Methods: start, stop, retry, runSingle, status, logs       │   │\n  32→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  33→│                           │                                         │\n  34→│  ┌────────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  35→│  │              DaemonLauncher (Daemon Mode)                    │   │\n  36→│  │  Methods: startDaemon, stopDaemon, queryDaemon              │   │\n  37→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  38→│                           │                                         │\n  39→│  ┌────────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  40→│  │              ErrorMapper (Error Handling)                    │   │\n  41→│  │  Maps exit codes, signals, timeouts → structured errors     │   │\n  42→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  43→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  44→                            │\n  45→┌───────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  46→│                    Infrastructure Layer (F-001)                     │\n  47→│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐    │\n  48→│  │ ScriptRunner    │  │ ConfigLoader    │  │ ErrorCodes      │    │\n  49→│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘    │\n  50→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  51→                            │\n  52→┌───────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  53→│                    Shell Scripts (dev-pipeline/)                    │\n  54→│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐    │\n  55→│  │ launch-daemon.sh│  │ run.sh /        │  │ retry-*.sh      │    │\n  56→│  │                 │  │ run-bugfix.sh   │  │ reset-*.sh      │    │\n  57→│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘    │\n  58→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  59→```\n  60→\n  61→## Component Design\n  62→\n  63→### 1. ProcessController (Core Module)\n  64→\n  65→**Location:** `src/services/process-controller.js`\n  66→\n  67→**Responsibilities:**\n  68→- Unified API for pipeline control actions\n  69→- Concurrency lock management\n  70→- State tracking and persistence\n  71→- Coordination of daemon operations\n  72→\n  73→**Dependencies:**\n  74→- `src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js` (executePipelineCommand)\n  75→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` (loadPipelineInfraConfig)\n  76→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` (INFRA_ERROR_CODES)\n  77→- `./daemon-launcher.js` (DaemonLauncher)\n  78→- `./error-mapper.js` (ErrorMapper)\n  79→\n  80→### 2. DaemonLauncher\n  81→\n  82→**Location:** `src/services/daemon-launcher.js`\n  83→\n  84→**Responsibilities:**\n  85→- Execute launch-daemon.sh with proper arguments\n  86→- Parse JSON output from daemon scripts\n  87→- Manage daemon lifecycle (start/stop/status/logs)\n  88→- Handle PID file operations\n  89→\n  90→**Dependencies:**\n  91→- `src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js`\n  92→- `fs` (for PID file verification)\n  93→\n  94→### 3. ErrorMapper\n  95→\n  96→**Location:** `src/services/error-mapper.js`\n  97→\n  98→**Responsibilities:**\n  99→- Map exit codes to structured errors\n 100→- Generate recovery hints\n 101→- Provide actionable error messages\n 102→\n 103→**Dependencies:**\n 104→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`\n 105→\n 106→### 4. StateTracker\n 107→\n 108→**Location:** `src/services/state-tracker.js`\n 109→\n 110→**Responsibilities:**\n 111→- Read/write pipeline state files\n 112→- Track running pipeline metadata\n 113→- Provide status aggregation\n 114→\n 115→**Dependencies:**\n 116→- `fs`, `path`\n 117→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js`\n 118→\n 119→### 5. MutexLock\n 120→\n 121→**Location:** `src/services/mutex-lock.js`\n 122→\n 123→**Responsibilities:**\n 124→- In-memory lock management per pipeline type\n 125→- Lock acquisition with timeout\n 126→- Automatic stale lock cleanup\n 127→\n 128→**Dependencies:** None (pure in-memory)\n 129→\n 130→## Interface Design\n 131→\n 132→### ProcessController API\n 133→\n 134→```typescript\n 135→// Type definitions for documentation\n 136→interface PipelineParams {\n 137→  pipelineType?: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 138→  targetId?: string;\n 139→  listPath?: string;\n 140→  daemon?: boolean;\n 141→  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 142→  timeoutMs?: number;\n 143→  force?: boolean;\n 144→  clean?: boolean;\n 145→}\n 146→\n 147→interface ProcessResult {\n 148→  ok: boolean;\n 149→  exitCode: number;\n 150→  status: 'success' | 'failed' | 'running' | 'stopped' | 'timed_out';\n 151→  message?: string;\n 152→  pid?: number;\n 153→  startTime?: string;\n 154→  logs?: string;\n 155→  progress?: ProgressInfo;\n 156→  error?: StructuredError;\n 157→}\n 158→\n 159→interface StructuredError {\n 160→  code: string;\n 161→  message: string;\n 162→  hint?: string;\n 163→  context?: Record<string, any>;\n 164→  recoverable: boolean;\n 165→}\n 166→\n 167→interface ProgressInfo {\n 168→  total: number;\n 169→  completed: number;\n 170→  inProgress: number;\n 171→  failed: number;\n 172→  pending: number;\n 173→  percent: number;\n 174→}\n 175→\n 176→interface ProcessController {\n 177→  // Start pipeline (all features/bugs)\n 178→  start(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n 179→  \n 180→  // Stop running pipeline\n 181→  stop(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n 182→  \n 183→  // Retry failed target\n 184→  retry(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n 185→  \n 186→  // Run single feature/bug\n 187→  runSingle(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n 188→  \n 189→  // Get status\n 190→  status(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n 191→  \n 192→  // Get logs\n 193→  logs(params: PipelineParams): Promise<ProcessResult>;\n 194→}\n 195→```\n 196→\n 197→### DaemonLauncher API\n 198→\n 199→```typescript\n 200→interface DaemonLauncher {\n 201→  start(params: {\n 202→    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 203→    listPath?: string;\n 204→    envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 205→  }): Promise<{ ok: boolean; pid: number; logFile: string }>;\n 206→  \n 207→  stop(params: {\n 208→    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 209→  }): Promise<{ ok: boolean; message: string }>;\n 210→  \n 211→  status(params: {\n 212→    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 213→  }): Promise<{\n 214→    running: boolean;\n 215→    pid?: number;\n 216→    startTime?: string;\n 217→    logFile?: string;\n 218→    progress?: ProgressInfo;\n 219→  }>;\n 220→  \n 221→  logs(params: {\n 222→    pipelineType: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 223→    lines?: number;\n 224→  }): Promise<string>;\n 225→}\n 226→```\n 227→\n 228→### ErrorMapper API\n 229→\n 230→```typescript\n 231→interface ErrorMapper {\n 232→  mapResult(raw: {\n 233→    exitCode?: number;\n 234→    signal?: string;\n 235→    timedOut?: boolean;\n 236→    stderr?: string;\n 237→  }): StructuredError | null;\n 238→  \n 239→  getLockError(currentPid: number, startTime: string): StructuredError;\n 240→  \n 241→  getScriptNotFoundError(scriptPath: string): StructuredError;\n 242→  \n 243→  getTimeoutError(timeoutMs: number): StructuredError;\n 244→}\n 245→```\n 246→\n 247→## Data Model\n 248→\n 249→### Pipeline State File\n 250→\n 251→**Path:** `dev-pipeline/state/.controller-state.json` (feature)\n 252→**Path:** `dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/.controller-state.json` (bugfix)\n 253→\n 254→```json\n 255→{\n 256→  \"version\": 1,\n 257→  \"pipelineType\": \"feature\",\n 258→  \"status\": \"running\",\n 259→  \"pid\": 12345,\n 260→  \"startedAt\": \"2026-03-12T10:30:00Z\",\n 261→  \"featureList\": \"/path/to/feature-list.json\",\n 262→  \"daemonMode\": true,\n 263→  \"envOverrides\": {\n 264→    \"MAX_RETRIES\": \"5\"\n 265→  },\n 266→  \"lastResult\": {\n 267→    \"ok\": false,\n 268→    \"exitCode\": 1,\n 269→    \"completedAt\": \"2026-03-12T09:15:00Z\",\n 270→    \"message\": \"Pipeline stopped by user\"\n 271→  }\n 272→}\n 273→```\n 274→\n 275→### Lock State (In-Memory)\n 276→\n 277→```javascript\n 278→const locks = {\n 279→  feature: {\n 280→    locked: false,\n 281→    pid: null,\n 282→    acquiredAt: null\n 283→  },\n 284→  bugfix: {\n 285→    locked: false,\n 286→    pid: null,\n 287→    acquiredAt: null\n 288→  }\n 289→};\n 290→```\n 291→\n 292→## User Story Mapping\n 293→\n 294→| User Story | Primary Component | Secondary Components |\n 295→|------------|-------------------|----------------------|\n 296→| US-1: Unified Control | ProcessController.start() | DaemonLauncher, ErrorMapper |\n 297→| US-2: Concurrent Protection | MutexLock | ProcessController, ErrorMapper |\n 298→| US-3: Daemon Mode | DaemonLauncher | ProcessController, StateTracker |\n 299→| US-4: Single Execution | ProcessController.runSingle() | ScriptRunner |\n 300→| US-5: Error Recovery | ErrorMapper | ProcessController |\n 301→| US-6: Handler Integration | ProcessController | Telegram handlers |\n 302→\n 303→## Testing Strategy\n 304→\n 305→### Unit Tests\n 306→\n 307→| Module | Test File | Coverage Target |\n 308→|--------|-----------|-----------------|\n 309→| ProcessController | `tests/services/process-controller.test.js` | 85% |\n 310→| DaemonLauncher | `tests/services/daemon-launcher.test.js` | 80% |\n 311→| ErrorMapper | `tests/services/error-mapper.test.js` | 90% |\n 312→| MutexLock | `tests/services/mutex-lock.test.js` | 90% |\n 313→| StateTracker | `tests/services/state-tracker.test.js` | 85% |\n 314→\n 315→**Key Test Scenarios:**\n 316→- Lock acquisition and release\n 317→- Concurrent start rejection\n 318→- Exit code mapping\n 319→- Timeout handling\n 320→- PID file parsing\n 321→- State persistence\n 322→\n 323→### Integration Tests\n 324→\n 325→**File:** `tests/integration/f004-process-controller.integration.test.js`\n 326→\n 327→| Scenario | Description |\n 328→|----------|-------------|\n 329→| I-001 | Start/stop feature pipeline daemon |\n 330→| I-002 | Start/stop bugfix pipeline daemon |\n 331→| I-003 | Concurrent start rejected with error |\n 332→| I-004 | Run single feature with clean |\n 333→| I-005 | Status query returns progress |\n 334→| I-006 | Error recovery with hints |\n 335→\n 336→### Test Fixtures\n 337→\n 338→- Mock script-runner for unit tests\n 339→- Test state files in `tests/fixtures/state/`\n 340→- Sample feature-list.json and bug-fix-list.json\n 341→\n 342→## File Structure\n 343→\n 344→```\n 345→src/\n 346→├── services/\n 347→│   ├── process-controller.js      # Core controller (NEW)\n 348→│   ├── daemon-launcher.js         # Daemon wrapper (NEW)\n 349→│   ├── error-mapper.js            # Error mapping (NEW)\n 350→│   ├── state-tracker.js           # State management (NEW)\n 351→│   ├── mutex-lock.js              # Concurrency lock (NEW)\n 352→│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js # Update to use ProcessController\n 353→│   └── plan-ingestion-service.js  # Unchanged\n 354→├── bot/commands/handlers/\n 355→│   ├── pipeline.js                # Update to use new API\n 356→│   ├── bugfix.js                  # Update to use new API\n 357→│   ├── status.js                  # Update to use new API\n 358→│   └── stop.js                    # Update to use new API\n 359→└── pipeline-infra/\n 360→    └── (unchanged from F-001)\n 361→\n 362→tests/\n 363→├── services/\n 364→│   ├── process-controller.test.js\n 365→│   ├── daemon-launcher.test.js\n 366→│   ├── error-mapper.test.js\n 367→│   ├── state-tracker.test.js\n 368→│   └── mutex-lock.test.js\n 369→├── integration/\n 370→│   └── f004-process-controller.integration.test.js\n 371→└── fixtures/\n 372→    └── state/\n 373→        ├── feature-state.json\n 374→        └── bugfix-state.json\n 375→```\n 376→\n 377→## Implementation Phases\n 378→\n 379→### Phase 1: Foundation (T-010 ~ T-029)\n 380→- MutexLock implementation\n 381→- ErrorMapper implementation\n 382→- StateTracker implementation\n 383→\n 384→### Phase 2: Core Controller (T-030 ~ T-059)\n 385→- ProcessController core logic\n 386→- DaemonLauncher integration\n 387→- API surface implementation\n 388→\n 389→### Phase 3: Integration (T-060 ~ T-089)\n 390→- Update pipeline-control-service\n 391→- Update Telegram handlers\n 392→- Integration testing\n 393→\n 394→### Phase 4: Polish (T-090 ~ T-099)\n 395→- Documentation updates\n 396→- Edge case handling\n 397→- Performance optimization\n 398→\n 399→## Risk Assessment\n 400→\n 401→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 402→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 403→| PID reuse causes false positive | Low | High | Include start time in validation |\n 404→| Lock deadlock on crash | Medium | High | Implement lock timeout (60s) + cleanup on status check |\n 405→| State file corruption | Low | High | Use atomic write + validation + default fallback |\n 406→| Script output format change | Low | Medium | Parse defensively with try-catch + fallback |\n 407→| Memory leak in long-running process | Low | Medium | No persistent state in memory, use files |\n 408→\n 409→## Dependencies Alignment\n 410→\n 411→### From F-001 (Infrastructure)\n 412→- `script-runner.js` - Used by DaemonLauncher\n 413→- `config-loader.js` - Configuration loading\n 414→- `error-codes.js` - Error code definitions\n 415→- `path-policy.js` - Path resolution\n 416→\n 417→### From F-002 (Command Router)\n 418→- Handler structure preserved\n 419→- Command metadata extended\n 420→- Formatter utilities reused\n 421→\n 422→### From F-003 (Plan Ingestion)\n 423→- `resolvePlanListPath()` used for list path resolution\n 424→- Plan version management integrated\n 425→\n 426→## Decisions Log\n 427→\n 428→| Date | Decision | Rationale |\n 429→|------|----------|-----------|\n 430→| 2026-03-12 | Use in-memory mutex over file-based lock | Single-machine deployment, simpler implementation |\n 431→| 2026-03-12 | Keep daemon scripts unchanged | Existing scripts work well, wrap in JS layer |\n 432→| 2026-03-12 | State files in dev-pipeline/state | Consistent with existing pipeline state location |\n 433→| 2026-03-12 | ProcessController as separate module from pipeline-control-service | Clean separation, backward compatibility |\n 434→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde68e81fd6885d5a22f36ce71dc2","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:39:10.938Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
