{"type":"user","uuid":"855e491d-8551-4c91-aa88-118f0eea6999","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde69d1cff5e5cc9568de6801804c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n   2→MODULE: runtime\n   3→PATH: src/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/config.js\n  11→- src/http/server.js\n  12→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n  13→- src/services/chat-service.js\n  14→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  15→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n  16→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n  17→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n  18→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n  19→- src/bot/telegram.js\n  20→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n  21→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n  22→\n  23→SUBDIRS:\n  24→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n  25→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n  26→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n  27→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n  28→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n  29→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n  30→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n  31→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n  32→\n  33→INTERFACES:\n  34→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n  35→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, text message relay\n  36→\n  37→TRAPS:\n  38→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n  39→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n  40→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n  41→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n  42→\n  43→DECISIONS:\n  44→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n  45→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n  46→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n  47→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n  48→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde68e81fd6885d5a22f36ce71dc2","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:40:03.351Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"857444ef-519a-4fc7-99de-bfac15553e4b","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde68e81fd6885d5a22f36ce71dc2","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. Let me compile the **Consistency Analysis Report** for F-004.\n\n---\n\n## Consistency Analysis Report: F-004 Pipeline Process Controller\n\n| ID | Category | Severity | Location(s) | Summary | Recommendation |\n|----|----------|----------|-------------|---------|----------------|\n| **F01** | Inconsistency | **CRITICAL** | spec.md L221 (D1), plan.md L430, spec.md L103-105 | Lock mechanism conflict: spec requires \"文件锁 + PID 校验\" but plan uses \"in-memory mutex\" | **Must resolve**: In-memory mutex cannot satisfy AC-7.3 (auto-release on process crash). Align plan to use file-based lock OR revise spec AC-7.3 |\n| **F02** | Inconsistency | **CRITICAL** | spec.md L163, plan.md L65, tasks.md L23,34,297,348 | Module naming conflict: spec uses `pipeline-controller.js`, plan/tasks use `process-controller.js` | Unify naming. Recommend `process-controller.js` (plan version) - update spec.md Scope Boundaries |\n| **F03** | Inconsistency | **HIGH** | plan.md L293-301 | User Story Mapping table completely misaligned with spec | Correct US mappings: US-2→Stop, US-3→Retry, US-5→Status, US-6→Logs, US-7→Concurrency, US-8→Error, US-9→Integration |\n| **F04** | Coverage Gap | **HIGH** | spec.md L139-142, tasks.md | NFR-1 Performance testing (<100ms, <50ms, <200ms) has no dedicated task | Add performance benchmark task or extend T-902 to include timing assertions |\n| **F05** | Coverage Gap | **HIGH** | spec.md L145-146, tasks.md | NFR-2 Reliability testing (锁机制可靠性 >99.9%) has no validation task | Add explicit reliability test task for MutexLock under crash simulation |\n| **F06** | Underspecification | **MEDIUM** | spec.md L145 | \"锁机制可靠性 > 99.9%\" - reliability metric undefined | Define measurement: e.g., \"successful lock acquisition/release cycles / total attempts over 1000 runs\" |\n| **F07** | Underspecification | **MEDIUM** | spec.md L74-75 | `currentFeature?` field format unspecified | Specify format: e.g., `{ id: string, name: string }` or just `string` (target ID) |\n| **F08** | Underspecification | **MEDIUM** | spec.md L89 | `lines` parameter has no upper limit | Add upper bound: e.g., `lines?: number (1-1000, default 100)` |\n| **F09** | Coverage Gap | **MEDIUM** | spec.md L153-156, tasks.md | NFR-4 Extensibility (new pipeline types) has no validation | Add task to verify config-driven pipeline type registration pattern |\n| **F10** | Ambiguity | **LOW** | spec.md L148 | \"函数长度 < 100 行\" - unclear if per-function or per-file | Clarify: \"Each exported function < 100 lines\" |\n| **F11** | Coverage Gap | **LOW** | spec.md L47-49 (US-3), spec.md L87-91 (US-6), tasks.md | US-3 (retry) and US-6 (logs) have no explicit handler update tasks | Verify T-100 pipeline-control-service update covers these; add handler tasks if needed |\n\n---\n\n### Coverage Summary\n\n| Requirement Key | Has Task? | Task IDs | Notes |\n|-----------------|-----------|----------|-------|\n| US-1: Unified Pipeline Start | ✅ | T-018, T-100, T-101 | Covered |\n| US-2: Pipeline Stop | ✅ | T-018, T-104 | Covered |\n| US-3: Target Retry | ⚠️ | T-019 | No handler task; relies on T-100 |\n| US-4: Run Single Feature | ✅ | T-019, T-105 | Covered |\n| US-5: Status Query | ✅ | T-018, T-103 | Covered |\n| US-6: Logs Query | ⚠️ | T-019 | No handler task; relies on T-100 |\n| US-7: Concurrency Protection | ✅ | T-010, T-011, T-201 | Covered |\n| US-8: Error Mapping | ✅ | T-012, T-013, T-106 | Covered |\n| US-9: Telegram Handler Integration | ✅ | T-100~T-106 | Covered |\n| NFR-1: Performance | ❌ | - | **No task** |\n| NFR-2: Reliability | ⚠️ | T-201 | Implicit via concurrent test, no explicit reliability metrics |\n| NFR-3: Maintainability | ✅ | T-900 | Covered |\n| NFR-4: Extensibility | ❌ | - | **No task** |\n\n---\n\n### Prizm Rules Alignment Issues\n\nNo explicit RULES or PATTERNS violations found. The root.prizm does not contain MUST/NEVER directives.\n\n---\n\n### Unmapped Tasks\n\nAll tasks map to spec requirements or project workflow needs. No orphan tasks found.\n\n---\n\n### Metrics\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Total Requirements | 13 (9 US + 4 NFR) |\n| Total Tasks | 24 |\n| Coverage % | **84.6%** (11/13 with ≥1 task) |\n| Ambiguity Count | 2 |\n| Duplication Count | 0 |\n| **Critical Issues** | **2** |\n| **High Issues** | **3** |\n| Medium Issues | 4 |\n| Low Issues | 2 |\n\n---\n\n## Next Actions\n\n⚠️ **CRITICAL ISSUES FOUND — Recommend resolving before `prizmkit.implement`**\n\n### Required Fixes:\n\n1. **F01 (Lock Mechanism)**: Choose ONE approach:\n   - **Option A (Recommended)**: Update plan.md Decision Log to use file-based lock + PID verification\n   - **Option B**: Revise spec.md D1 and AC-7.3 to accept in-memory mutex with timeout cleanup\n\n2. **F02 (Module Naming)**: Update spec.md L163 to use `process-controller.js` to match plan/tasks\n\n3. **F03 (User Story Mapping)**: Correct the table in plan.md L293-301 to accurately reflect spec.md user story definitions\n\n### Recommended Fixes:\n\n4. **F04-F05 (NFR Coverage)**: Add explicit performance and reliability testing tasks\n\n5. **F06-F08 (Underspecification)**: Clarify ambiguous metrics and data formats in spec.md\n\n---\n\n## COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n\n**Phase 4 Cross-Check Complete**\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Feature | F-004: Pipeline Process Controller |\n| Analysis Type | prizmkit.analyze (Phase 4) |\n| Judgment | **NEEDS_FIXES** |\n| Critical Issues | 2 |\n| High Issues | 3 |\n| Recommendation | Return to PM for artifact alignment before implementation |\n\n**Issue Report sent to Coordinator**: F01, F02, F03 require PM resolution.\n\n[Agent ID: agent-85604260]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde68e81fd6885d5a22f36ce71dc2","__timestam