ces/pipeline-controller.js\n 101→- [ ] [T-144] [P] Write unit tests for runSingle — file: tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js\n 102→- [ ] [T-145] Write integration test for US-4 — file: tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js\n 103→\n 104→### US-5: Status Query (T-150 ~ T-159)\n 105→\n 106→- [ ] [T-150] Implement getStatus skeleton — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 107→- [ ] [T-151] Integrate state-manager for daemon/pipeline state — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 108→- [ ] [T-152] Add currentFeature and startedAt from current-session — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 109→- [ ] [T-153] Include lastResult when not running — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 110→- [ ] [T-154] Include lockInfo from lock-manager — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 111→- [ ] [T-155] [P] Write unit tests for getStatus — file: tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js\n 112→- [ ] [T-156] Write integration test for US-5 — file: tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js\n 113→\n 114→### US-6: Logs Query (T-160 ~ T-169)\n 115→\n 116→- [ ] [T-160] Implement getLogs skeleton — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 117→- [ ] [T-161] Read log file with line limit — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 118→- [ ] [T-162] Handle missing log file gracefully — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 119→- [ ] [T-163] Return logPath in result — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 120→- [ ] [T-164] [P] Write unit tests for getLogs — file: tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js\n 121→- [ ] [T-165] Write integration test for US-6 — file: tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js\n 122→\n 123→### US-7: Concurrency Protection (T-170 ~ T-179)\n 124→\n 125→- [ ] [T-170] Integrate lock-manager in startPipeline — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 126→- [ ] [T-171] Add forceUnlock admin method — file: src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n 127→- [