{"type":"user","uuid":"d0c9a930-daff-43f8-a766-15616aaf1cfa","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde6ae0c55a98ff7556dcc5457665","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-004: Pipeline Process Controller\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→构建 pipeline 进程控制层，统一封装 dev-pipeline/run.sh 与 run-bugfix.sh 的启动、停止、重试、单特性执行与后台守护模式。该层提供稳定 API 给 Telegram 命令路由调用，并负责并发锁、超时、退出码映射与异常恢复。目标是把当前\"终端操作脚本\"能力抽象为\"程序可调用控制接口\"。\n   6→\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→## User Stories\n  10→\n  11→### US-1: Unified Pipeline Start\n  12→\n  13→**As a** Telegram 用户或系统集成者  \n  14→**I want** 通过统一的控制接口启动 feature pipeline 或 bugfix pipeline  \n  15→**So that** 我不需要关心底层脚本的差异，且能获得标准化的执行结果\n  16→\n  17→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  18→- AC-1.1: `startPipeline({ type: 'feature' | 'bugfix', targetId?, listPath?, daemon?: boolean })` 可启动指定类型管道\n  19→- AC-1.2: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, runId, pid?, message, errorCode? }`\n  20→- AC-1.3: 若指定 `daemon: true`，以后台守护模式启动，返回 PID\n  21→- AC-1.4: 若管道已在运行中（并发锁检查失败），返回 `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED` 错误\n  22→\n  23→---\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: Pipeline Stop\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 运维人员  \n  28→**I want** 通过控制接口停止正在运行的管道  \n  29→**So that** 我可以从 Telegram 或 API 中止异常的管道执行\n  30→\n  31→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  32→- AC-2.1: `stopPipeline({ type: 'feature' | 'bugfix' })` 可停止指定类型的守护进程\n  33→- AC-2.2: 若进程已停止，返回 `ALREADY_STOPPED` 状态而非错误\n  34→- AC-2.3: 停止操作有 10 秒超时，超时后强制终止\n  35→- AC-2.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, previousPid, message }`\n  36→\n  37→---\n  38→\n  39→### US-3: Target Retry\n  40→\n  41→**As a** 开发者  \n  42→**I want** 重试某个失败的 feature 或 bugfix 目标  \n  43→**So that** 我可以针对单个失败项进行修复而不影响其他已完成的工作\n  44→\n  45→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  46→- AC-3.1: `retryTarget({ type, targetId, listPath? })` 可重试指定目标\n  47→- AC-3.2: 若目标不存在或状态不允许可重试，返回明确错误\n  48→- AC-3.3: 支持前台和后台模式\n  49→- AC-3.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, targetId, message }`\n  50→\n  51→---\n  52→\n  53→### US-4: Run Single Feature\n  54→\n  55→**As a** 开发者  \n  56→**I want** 单独运行某个特定的 feature 或 bugfix  \n  57→**So that** 我可以测试或调试单个工作项而不运行整个队列\n  58→\n  59→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  60→- AC-4.1: `runSingle({ type, targetId, listPath? })` 可执行单个目标\n  61→- AC-4.2: 执行完成后返回完整的执行结果（含 stdout/stderr）\n  62→- AC-4.3: 支持超时配置\n  63→- AC-4.4: 不影响管道整体状态（独立执行）\n  64→\n  65→---\n  66→\n  67→### US-5: Status Query\n  68→\n  69→**As a** 运维人员  \n  70→**I want** 查询管道的当前状态  \n  71→**So that** 我可以了解系统运行情况并做出决策\n  72→\n  73→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  74→- AC-5.1: `getPipelineStatus({ type })` 返回管道状态对象\n  75→- AC-5.2: 状态对象包含 `{ isRunning, pid?, currentFeature?, startedAt?, lastResult? }`\n  76→- AC-5.3: 若有运行中的目标，包含 `currentFeature` 和 `startedAt`\n  77→- AC-5.4: 若无运行中管道，返回 `lastResult`（最近一次执行结果）\n  78→\n  79→---\n  80→\n  81→### US-6: Logs Query\n  82→\n  83→**As a** 运维人员  \n  84→**I want** 获取管道执行日志  \n  85→**So that** 我可以诊断问题或监控执行进度\n  86→\n  87→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  88→- AC-6.1: `getPipelineLogs({ type, lines?: number })` 返回日志内容\n  89→- AC-6.2: 默认返回最近 100 行，可通过 `lines` 参数调整\n  90→- AC-6.3: 日志不存在时返回空字符串而非错误\n  91→- AC-6.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, logs, logPath }`\n  92→\n  93→---\n  94→\n  95→### US-7: Concurrency Protection\n  96→\n  97→**As a** 系统管理员  \n  98→**I want** 防止多个管道实例同时运行  \n  99→**So that** 系统资源不被过度占用且状态文件不会冲突\n 100→\n 101→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 102→- AC-7.1: 同类型管道同一时间只能有一个实例运行\n 103→- AC-7.2: 锁获取失败时返回 `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED` 错误，含当前持有者信息\n 104→- AC-7.3: 锁在进程异常退出时自动释放（通过 PID 检测）\n 105→- AC-7.4: 提供 `forceUnlock({ type })` 用于强制释放锁（管理员操作）\n 106→\n 107→---\n 108→\n 109→### US-8: Error Mapping\n 110→\n 111→**As a** Telegram handler 开发者  \n 112→**I want** 所有错误都有结构化的错误码和消息  \n 113→**So that** 我可以向用户展示友好的错误提示而非原始错误堆栈\n 114→\n 115→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 116→- AC-8.1: 所有错误返回 `{ ok: false, errorCode: string, message: string, hint?: string }`\n 117→- AC-8.2: 错误码覆盖: `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED`, `SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND`, `EXEC_TIMEOUT`, `EXEC_FAILED`, `INVALID_TARGET`, `PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING`, `ALREADY_STOPPED`\n 118→- AC-8.3: 超时错误包含超时时长信息\n 119→- AC-8.4: 脚本缺失错误包含脚本路径\n 120→\n 121→---\n 122→\n 123→### US-9: Telegram Handler Integration\n 124→\n 125→**As a** Telegram bot 开发者  \n 126→**I want** 控制层接口可直接被 Telegram handler 调用  \n 127→**So that** 命令路由实现变得简单且不依赖终端交互\n 128→\n 129→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 130→- AC-9.1: 所有方法返回 Promise，可被 async/await 调用\n 131→- AC-9.2: 无需传递 process.stdin/stdout 依赖\n 132→- AC-9.3: 执行结果可通过 JSON 序列化传输\n 133→- AC-9.4: 提供 `createPipelineController()` 工厂函数，支持依赖注入\n 134→\n 135→---\n 136→\n 137→## Non-Functional Requirements\n 138→\n 139→### NFR-1: Performance\n 140→- 控制接口响应时间 < 100ms（不含脚本执行时间）\n 141→- 状态查询 < 50ms\n 142→- 日志读取（100 行）< 200ms\n 143→\n 144→### NFR-2: Reliability\n 145→- 锁机制可靠性 > 99.9%（无死锁场景）\n 146→- 进程异常退出时资源清理率 100%\n 147→\n 148→### NFR-3: Maintainability\n 149→- 核心模块单文件，函数长度 < 100 行\n 150→- 错误码定义在单一文件中管理\n 151→- 测试覆盖率 > 90%\n 152→\n 153→### NFR-4: Extensibility\n 154→- 支持未来添加新的 pipeline 类型（如 `planner`）\n 155→- 错误码可扩展\n 156→- 状态模型可扩展\n 157→\n 158→---\n 159→\n 160→## Scope Boundaries\n 161→\n 162→### In Scope\n 163→- Pipeline 控制器核心模块 (`src/services/pipeline-controller.js`)\n 164→- 并发锁管理器 (`src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js`)\n 165→- 状态管理器 (`src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js`)\n 166→- 错误码扩展 (`src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`)\n 167→- 与现有 daemon 脚本的集成\n 168→- 单元测试与集成测试\n 169→\n 170→### Out of Scope\n 171→- Telegram 命令路由实现（已在 F-002 完成）\n 172→- Pipeline 内部逻辑修改\n 173→- Web UI\n 174→- 数据库持久化（继续使用 JSON 文件）\n 175→- 认证授权（由上层路由处理）\n 176→\n 177→---\n 178→\n 179→## Dependencies\n 180→\n 181→| Dependency | Type | Status | Notes |\n 182→|------------|------|--------|-------|\n 183→| F-001 | Feature | completed | 提供基础架构 (script-runner, error-codes, path-policy) |\n 184→| F-002 | Feature | completed | 提供命令路由层 (将调用 F-004 API) |\n 185→| launch-daemon.sh | Script | existing | Feature daemon 管理脚本 |\n 186→| launch-bugfix-daemon.sh | Script | existing | Bugfix daemon 管理脚本 |\n 187→| retry-feature.sh | Script | existing | Feature 重试脚本 |\n 188→| retry-bug.sh | Script | existing | Bugfix 重试脚本 |\n 189→\n 190→---\n 191→\n 192→## Risks\n 193→\n 194→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 195→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 196→| 并发锁实现复杂导致死锁 | Medium | High | 使用简单的文件锁 + PID 检测，避免复杂同步原语 |\n 197→| Daemon 脚本输出格式变化 | Low | Medium | 建立脚本输出契约，添加输出解析测试 |\n 198→| 大日志文件读取阻塞 | Low | Medium | 使用流式读取或限制读取行数 |\n 199→| 跨平台兼容性（macOS/Linux） | Low | Low | 主要使用 Node.js API，脚本在 WSL/Git Bash 兼容 |\n 200→\n 201→---\n 202→\n 203→## Technical Notes\n 204→\n 205→### 现有基础设施\n 206→- `script-runner.js` 已提供基本的命令执行和错误映射\n 207→- `pipeline-control-service.js` 已提供基础 API，但缺少并发保护和 daemon 模式\n 208→- `launch-daemon.sh` 和 `launch-bugfix-daemon.sh` 提供 PID 管理和日志合并\n 209→\n 210→### 设计方向\n 211→- 扩展 `pipeline-control-service.js` 或创建新模块 `pipeline-controller.js`\n 212→- 锁管理器使用文件锁 (`flock` 或 `.lock` 文件 + PID 校验)\n 213→- 状态管理器读取现有的 `pipeline.json` 和 `.pipeline-meta.json`\n 214→\n 215→---\n 216→\n 217→## Decisions\n 218→\n 219→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 220→|----|------|----------|\n 221→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | 使用文件锁 + PID 校验实现并发保护，避免引入外部依赖 |\n 222→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 创建独立的 `pipeline-controller.js` 模块，而非扩展现有 `pipeline-control-service.js`，以保持职责清晰 |\n 223→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 复用现有 daemon 脚本的输出格式，不做脚本修改 |\n 224→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6a72d69f73a81ac88ee3c8122b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:41:13.338Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"a2057369-3a7a-412d-902a-6dfe3879b4c8","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde6ae2b9104d9365347b68e8d809","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-004: Pipeline Process Controller — Technical Plan\n   2→\n   3→## 1. Architecture Overview\n   4→\n   5→```\n   6→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   7→│                         Telegram Command Router (F-002)                      │\n   8→│                    src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js                            │\n   9→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  10→                                      │\n  11→                                      ▼\n  12→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  13→│                      Pipeline Controller (NEW)                               │\n  14→│                    src/services/pipeline-controller.js                       │\n  15→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n  16→│  │ • startPipeline()  • stopPipeline()  • retryTarget()                │    │\n  17→│  │ • runSingle()      • getStatus()      • getLogs()                   │    │\n  18→│  │ • forceUnlock()    • acquireLock()    • releaseLock()               │    │\n  19→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n  20→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  21→                    │                      │                      │\n  22→                    ▼                      ▼                      ▼\n  23→┌─────────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────┐\n  24→│    Lock Manager (NEW)   │ │   State Manager (NEW)   │ │   Script Runner     │\n  25→│  src/pipeline-infra/    │ │  src/pipeline-infra/    │ │    (Existing)       │\n  26→│    lock-manager.js      │ │    state-manager.js     │ │  script-runner.js   │\n  27→├─────────────────────────┤ ├─────────────────────────┤ ├─────────────────────┤\n  28→│ • acquireLock()         │ │ • readDaemonMeta()      │ │ • buildPipelineCmd()│\n  29→│ • releaseLock()         │ │ • readPipelineState()   │ │ • executePipeline() │\n  30→│ • isLocked()            │ │ • readCurrentSession()  │ │ • normalizeResult() │\n  31→│ • forceUnlock()         │ │ • writeDaemonMeta()     │ │                     │\n  32→│ • validateLock()        │ │ • getLastResult()       │ │                     │\n  33→└─────────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────┘\n  34→                    │                      │                      │\n  35→                    └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘\n  36→                                           ▼\n  37→                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  38→                    │                  dev-pipeline/scripts/                  │\n  39→                    │  launch-daemon.sh, launch-bugfix-daemon.sh              │\n  40→                    │  run.sh, run-bugfix.sh, retry-*.sh, reset-*.sh          │\n  41→                    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  42→                                           │\n  43→                                           ▼\n  44→                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  45→                    │                       State Files                       │\n  46→                    │  state/.pipeline.pid, state/pipeline.json               │\n  47→                    │  state/.pipeline-meta.json, state/pipeline-daemon.log   │\n  48→                    │  bugfix-state/... (mirror structure)                    │\n  49→                    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  50→```\n  51→\n  52→---\n  53→\n  54→## 2. Component Design\n  55→\n  56→### 2.1 Pipeline Controller (`src/services/pipeline-controller.js`)\n  57→\n  58→**职责**: 高层控制 API 入口，协调 lock-manager、state-manager、script-runner\n  59→\n  60→**核心方法**:\n  61→\n  62→```javascript\n  63→export function createPipelineController(options = {}) {\n  64→  const {\n  65→    lockManager = createLockManager(),\n  66→    stateManager = createStateManager(),\n  67→    scriptRunner = executePipelineCommand,\n  68→    config = loadPipelineInfraConfig()\n  69→  } = options;\n  70→\n  71→  return {\n  72→    // Lifecycle\n  73→    startPipeline(params),\n  74→    stopPipeline(params),\n  75→    \n  76→    // Target Operations\n  77→    retryTarget(params),\n  78→    runSingle(params),\n  79→    \n  80→    // Query\n  81→    getStatus(params),\n  82→    getLogs(params),\n  83→    \n  84→    // Admin\n  85→    forceUnlock(params),\n  86→    \n  87→    // Internal\n  88→    _acquireLock(type),\n  89→    _releaseLock(type),\n  90→  };\n  91→}\n  92→```\n  93→\n  94→### 2.2 Lock Manager (`src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js`)\n  95→\n  96→**职责**: 并发锁管理，防止同类型管道同时运行\n  97→\n  98→**实现策略**: 文件锁 + PID 校验\n  99→- 锁文件: `state/.pipeline.lock` / `bugfix-state/.pipeline.lock`\n 100→- 锁内容: `{ pid, acquiredAt, type }`\n 101→- 校验: 检查锁文件 + 验证 PID 是否存活\n 102→\n 103→**核心方法**:\n 104→\n 105→```javascript\n 106→export function createLockManager(options = {}) {\n 107→  const { config = loadPipelineInfraConfig() } = options;\n 108→  \n 109→  return {\n 110→    async acquireLock(type, pid = process.pid),\n 111→    async releaseLock(type, pid = process.pid),\n 112→    async isLocked(type),\n 113→    async validateLock(type),\n 114→    async forceUnlock(type),\n 115→    async getLockInfo(type),\n 116→  };\n 117→}\n 118→```\n 119→\n 120→### 2.3 State Manager (`src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js`)\n 121→\n 122→**职责**: 读取和管理管道状态文件\n 123→\n 124→**核心方法**:\n 125→\n 126→```javascript\n 127→export function createStateManager(options = {}) {\n 128→  const { config = loadPipelineInfraConfig() } = options;\n 129→  \n 130→  return {\n 131→    // Read Operations\n 132→    async readDaemonMeta(type),\n 133→    async readPipelineState(type),\n 134→    async readCurrentSession(type),\n 135→    async getLastResult(type),\n 136→    \n 137→    // Write Operations\n 138→    async writeDaemonMeta(type, meta),\n 139→    async writeLastResult(type, result),\n 140→    \n 141→    // Query\n 142→    async isDaemonRunning(type),\n 143→    async getDaemonPid(type),\n 144→  };\n 145→}\n 146→```\n 147→\n 148→### 2.4 Error Codes Extension (`src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`)\n 149→\n 150→**新增错误码**:\n 151→\n 152→```javascript\n 153→export const INFRA_ERROR_CODES = Object.freeze({\n 154→  // Existing\n 155→  CONFIG_MISSING: 'CONFIG_MISSING',\n 156→  CONFIG_INVALID: 'CONFIG_INVALID',\n 157→  PATH_INVALID: 'PATH_INVALID',\n 158→  SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND: 'SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND',\n 159→  EXEC_TIMEOUT: 'EXEC_TIMEOUT',\n 160→  EXEC_FAILED: 'EXEC_FAILED',\n 161→  \n 162→  // NEW for F-004\n 163→  LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED: 'LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED',\n 164→  ALREADY_STOPPED: 'ALREADY_STOPPED',\n 165→  PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING: 'PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING',\n 166→  INVALID_TARGET: 'INVALID_TARGET',\n 167→  TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE: 'TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE',\n 168→  DAEMON_START_FAILED: 'DAEMON_START_FAILED',\n 169→});\n 170→```\n 171→\n 172→---\n 173→\n 174→## 3. Interface Design\n 175→\n 176→### 3.1 Pipeline Controller API\n 177→\n 178→#### `startPipeline(params)`\n 179→\n 180→**Input**:\n 181→```typescript\n 182→interface StartPipelineParams {\n 183→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 184→  targetId?: string;        // Optional: start with specific target\n 185→  listPath?: string;        // Optional: override default list path\n 186→  daemon?: boolean;         // Default: true for startPipeline\n 187→  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 188→  timeoutMs?: number;\n 189→}\n 190→```\n 191→\n 192→**Output**:\n 193→```typescript\n 194→interface PipelineResult {\n 195→  ok: boolean;\n 196→  runId?: string;\n 197→  pid?: number;\n 198→  message: string;\n 199→  errorCode?: string;\n 200→  hint?: string;\n 201→  context?: Record<string, unknown>;\n 202→}\n 203→```\n 204→\n 205→**Behavior**:\n 206→1. Acquire lock for pipeline type\n 207→2. If daemon mode, call `launch-daemon.sh start`\n 208→3. If foreground, call `run.sh run [targetId]`\n 209→4. Return result with PID (daemon) or execution result (foreground)\n 210→\n 211→---\n 212→\n 213→#### `stopPipeline(params)`\n 214→\n 215→**Input**:\n 216→```typescript\n 217→interface StopPipelineParams {\n 218→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 219→  timeoutMs?: number;       // Default: 10000\n 220→}\n 221→```\n 222→\n 223→**Output**:\n 224→```typescript\n 225→interface StopResult {\n 226→  ok: boolean;\n 227→  previousPid?: number;\n 228→  message: string;\n 229→  errorCode?: string;\n 230→}\n 231→```\n 232→\n 233→**Behavior**:\n 234→1. Check if daemon is running\n 235→2. Call `launch-daemon.sh stop`\n 236→3. Wait for process termination (with timeout)\n 237→4. Release lock\n 238→5. Return previous PID and status\n 239→\n 240→---\n 241→\n 242→#### `retryTarget(params)`\n 243→\n 244→**Input**:\n 245→```typescript\n 246→interface RetryTargetParams {\n 247→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 248→  targetId: string;\n 249→  listPath?: string;\n 250→  daemon?: boolean;\n 251→  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 252→}\n 253→```\n 254→\n 255→**Output**: Same as `startPipeline()`\n 256→\n 257→**Behavior**:\n 258→1. Validate target exists and is retryable\n 259→2. If daemon mode, acquire lock first\n 260→3. Execute retry script\n 261→4. Return result\n 262→\n 263→---\n 264→\n 265→#### `runSingle(params)`\n 266→\n 267→**Input**:\n 268→```typescript\n 269→interface RunSingleParams {\n 270→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 271→  targetId: string;\n 272→  listPath?: string;\n 273→  timeoutMs?: number;\n 274→  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 275→}\n 276→```\n 277→\n 278→**Output**:\n 279→```typescript\n 280→interface RunSingleResult {\n 281→  ok: boolean;\n 282→  targetId: string;\n 283→  message: string;\n 284→  stdout?: string;\n 285→  stderr?: string;\n 286→  exitCode?: number;\n 287→  errorCode?: string;\n 288→}\n 289→```\n 290→\n 291→**Behavior**:\n 292→1. Execute single target in foreground\n 293→2. Do NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n 294→3. Return full execution details\n 295→\n 296→---\n 297→\n 298→#### `getStatus(params)`\n 299→\n 300→**Input**:\n 301→```typescript\n 302→interface GetStatusParams {\n 303→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 304→}\n 305→```\n 306→\n 307→**Output**:\n 308→```typescript\n 309→interface StatusResult {\n 310→  ok: boolean;\n 311→  isRunning: boolean;\n 312→  pid?: number;\n 313→  currentFeature?: string;\n 314→  startedAt?: string;\n 315→  lastResult?: LastResult;\n 316→  lockInfo?: LockInfo;\n 317→  message: string;\n 318→}\n 319→\n 320→interface LastResult {\n 321→  runId: string;\n 322→  completedAt: string;\n 323→  status: 'success' | 'failed' | 'partial';\n 324→  featuresTotal: number;\n 325→  featuresCompleted: number;\n 326→}\n 327→\n 328→interface LockInfo {\n 329→  pid: number;\n 330→  acquiredAt: string;\n 331→}\n 332→```\n 333→\n 334→---\n 335→\n 336→#### `getLogs(params)`\n 337→\n 338→**Input**:\n 339→```typescript\n 340→interface GetLogsParams {\n 341→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 342→  lines?: number;           // Default: 100\n 343→  follow?: boolean;         // Not implemented in v1\n 344→}\n 345→```\n 346→\n 347→**Output**:\n 348→```typescript\n 349→interface LogsResult {\n 350→  ok: boolean;\n 351→  logs: string;\n 352→  logPath: string;\n 353→  lines: number;\n 354→  message: string;\n 355→}\n 356→```\n 357→\n 358→---\n 359→\n 360→#### `forceUnlock(params)`\n 361→\n 362→**Input**:\n 363→```typescript\n 364→interface ForceUnlockParams {\n 365→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 366→}\n 367→```\n 368→\n 369→**Output**:\n 370→```typescript\n 371→interface ForceUnlockResult {\n 372→  ok: boolean;\n 373→  previousPid?: number;\n 374→  message: string;\n 375→}\n 376→```\n 377→\n 378→**Behavior**:\n 379→1. Get lock info\n 380→2. Remove lock file\n 381→3. Return previous lock info\n 382→\n 383→---\n 384→\n 385→### 3.2 Lock Manager API\n 386→\n 387→#### `acquireLock(type, pid?)`\n 388→\n 389→**Input**:\n 390→- `type`: 'feature' | 'bugfix'\n 391→- `pid`: number (default: process.pid)\n 392→\n 393→**Output**:\n 394→```typescript\n 395→interface LockResult {\n 396→  ok: boolean;\n 397→  lockPath: string;\n 398→  errorCode?: 'LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED';\n 399→  currentHolder?: LockInfo;\n 400→}\n 401→```\n 402→\n 403→**Implementation**:\n 404→1. Check if lock file exists\n 405→2. If exists, validate PID is dead\n 406→3. Write lock file atomically\n 407→4. Return result\n 408→\n 409→---\n 410→\n 411→### 3.3 State Manager API\n 412→\n 413→#### `readDaemonMeta(type)`\n 414→\n 415→**Output**:\n 416→```typescript\n 417→interface DaemonMeta {\n 418→  pid: number;\n 419→  started_at: string;\n 420→  feature_list: string;\n 421→  env_overrides: string;\n 422→  log_file: string;\n 423→}\n 424→```\n 425→\n 426→#### `readPipelineState(type)`\n 427→\n 428→**Output**:\n 429→```typescript\n 430→interface PipelineState {\n 431→  run_id: string;\n 432→  status: 'running' | 'paused' | 'completed' | 'failed';\n 433→  feature_list_path: string;\n 434→  created_at: string;\n 435→  total_features: number;\n 436→  completed_features: number;\n 437→  paused_at?: string;\n 438→}\n 439→```\n 440→\n 441→#### `isDaemonRunning(type)`\n 442→\n 443→**Output**: `boolean`\n 444→\n 445→**Implementation**:\n 446→1. Read daemon meta\n 447→2. Check if PID is alive via `process.kill(pid, 0)`\n 448→3. Return boolean\n 449→\n 450→---\n 451→\n 452→## 4. Data Model\n 453→\n 454→### 4.1 Lock File Schema\n 455→\n 456→**Path**: `{stateDir}/.pipeline.lock` or `bugfix-state/.pipeline.lock`\n 457→\n 458→```json\n 459→{\n 460→  \"pid\": 12345,\n 461→  \"acquiredAt\": \"2026-03-12T10:30:00Z\",\n 462→  \"type\": \"feature\",\n 463→  \"hostname\": \"dev-machine\"\n 464→}\n 465→```\n 466→\n 467→### 4.2 Last Result Schema (NEW)\n 468→\n 469→**Path**: `{stateDir}/.last-result.json` or `bugfix-state/.last-result.json`\n 470→\n 471→```json\n 472→{\n 473→  \"runId\": \"run-20260312-103000\",\n 474→  \"completedAt\": \"2026-03-12T12:45:00Z\",\n 475→  \"status\": \"success\",\n 476→  \"featuresTotal\": 8,\n 477→  \"featuresCompleted\": 8,\n 478→  \"exitCode\": 0,\n 479→  \"message\": \"Pipeline completed successfully\"\n 480→}\n 481→```\n 482→\n 483→### 4.3 State File Integration\n 484→\n 485→Reuse existing state files:\n 486→- `state/pipeline.json` → `readPipelineState('feature')`\n 487→- `state/.pipeline-meta.json` → `readDaemonMeta('feature')`\n 488→- `state/current-session.json` → `readCurrentSession('feature')`\n 489→- Mirror paths for `bugfix-state/`\n 490→\n 491→---\n 492→\n 493→## 5. Module Dependencies\n 494→\n 495→```\n 496→pipeline-controller.js\n 497→    ├── lock-manager.js\n 498→    ├── state-manager.js\n 499→    ├── script-runner.js (existing)\n 500→    ├── config-loader.js (existing)\n 501→    └── error-codes.js (extended)\n 502→\n 503→lock-manager.js\n 504→    ├── path-policy.js (existing)\n 505→    └── config-loader.js (existing)\n 506→\n 507→state-manager.js\n 508→    ├── path-policy.js (existing)\n 509→    └── config-loader.js (existing)\n 510→```\n 511→\n 512→---\n 513→\n 514→## 6. Testing Strategy\n 515→\n 516→### 6.1 Unit Tests\n 517→\n 518→| Module | Test File | Focus |\n 519→|--------|-----------|-------|\n 520→| lock-manager.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` | Lock acquire/release, PID validation, stale lock cleanup |\n 521→| state-manager.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js` | State file reading, JSON parsing, missing file handling |\n 522→| pipeline-controller.js | `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js` | All API methods, error handling, mock dependencies |\n 523→| error-codes.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/error-codes.test.js` | Error code validation, error factory |\n 524→\n 525→### 6.2 Integration Tests\n 526→\n 527→**File**: `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n 528→\n 529→| Test Case | Description |\n 530→|-----------|-------------|\n 531→| Full Lifecycle | startPipeline → getStatus → stopPipeline |\n 532→| Lock Behavior | Concurrent start attempts, lock release on stop |\n 533→| Error Recovery | Stop non-running pipeline, retry invalid target |\n 534→| State Persistence | Verify state files after operations |\n 535→| Daemon Mode | Start daemon, query PID, verify log output |\n 536→\n 537→### 6.3 Test Coverage Target\n 538→\n 539→- Core modules: > 90% branch coverage\n 540→- Integration tests: All user stories covered\n 541→\n 542→---\n 543→\n 544→## 7. Risk Assessment\n 545→\n 546→| Risk | Mitigation | Owner |\n 547→|------|------------|-------|\n 548→| Lock file corruption | Atomic write via temp file + rename, validate JSON on read | Dev |\n 549→| PID reuse race condition | Include timestamp in lock, validate with short timeout | Dev |\n 550→| Large log file blocking | Use `fs.createReadStream` with line limit | Dev |\n 551→| Test environment isolation | Use temp directories for state files in tests | Dev |\n 552→| Backward compatibility with existing scripts | No script modifications, only wrappers | Dev |\n 553→\n 554→---\n 555→\n 556→## 8. User Story to Component Mapping\n 557→\n 558→| User Story | Primary Component | Supporting Components |\n 559→|------------|-------------------|----------------------|\n 560→| US-1: Unified Pipeline Start | pipeline-controller.startPipeline() | lock-manager, script-runner |\n 561→| US-2: Pipeline Stop | pipeline-controller.stopPipeline() | state-manager, lock-manager |\n 562→| US-3: Target Retry | pipeline-controller.retryTarget() | script-runner, state-manager |\n 563→| US-4: Run Single Feature | pipeline-controller.runSingle() | script-runner |\n 564→| US-5: Status Query | pipeline-controller.getStatus() | state-manager, lock-manager |\n 565→| US-6: Logs Query | pipeline-controller.getLogs() | state-manager |\n 566→| US-7: Concurrency Protection | lock-manager | state-manager |\n 567→| US-8: Error Mapping | error-codes.js (extended) | pipeline-controller |\n 568→| US-9: Telegram Handler Integration | pipeline-controller API design | All |\n 569→\n 570→---\n 571→\n 572→## 9. Implementation Phases\n 573→\n 574→### Phase 1: Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n 575→- Setup test infrastructure\n 576→- Extend error codes\n 577→- Create lock-manager\n 578→- Create state-manager\n 579→\n 580→### Phase 2: Core Controller (T-010 ~ T-099)\n 581→- Implement pipeline-controller skeleton\n 582→- Implement each API method\n 583→- Integrate with existing script-runner\n 584→\n 585→### Phase 3: User Story Implementation (T-100+)\n 586→- US-1: startPipeline\n 587→- US-2: stopPipeline\n 588→- US-3: retryTarget\n 589→- US-4: runSingle\n 590→- US-5: getStatus\n 591→- US-6: getLogs\n 592→- US-7: Lock integration\n 593→- US-8: Error mapping\n 594→- US-9: Integration tests\n 595→\n 596→### Phase 4: Polish (T-900+)\n 597→- Documentation updates\n 598→- Performance optimization\n 599→- Edge case handling\n 600→\n 601→---\n 602→\n 603→## 10. Key Decisions\n 604→\n 605→| ID | Decision | Rationale |\n 606→|----|----------|-----------|\n 607→| D1 | Separate lock-manager module | Single responsibility, easier testing |\n 608→| D2 | File-based locks with PID validation | No external dependencies, simple and reliable |\n 609→| D3 | Reuse existing state files | Backward compatible, no migration needed |\n 610→| D4 | New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service | Clear separation, avoid breaking existing API |\n 611→| D5 | runSingle does NOT acquire lock | Independent execution use case |\n 612→| D6 | Last result stored in separate file | Don't modify existing state file schema |\n 613→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde6a72d69f73a81ac88ee3c8122b","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:41:13.350Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
