{"type":"user","uuid":"561f1d40-05de-4b0a-ad1b-8e415b88fe21","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde7ad5ab5397b7a7f59a0a4b0f14","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizmkit-code-review\n   3→description: Code review against spec, plan, and best practices. Read-only analysis with severity ratings. Invoke after implementation or when user requests review. (project)\n   4→---\n   5→\n   6→# PrizmKit Code Review\n   7→\n   8→Perform a comprehensive code review against the feature spec, implementation plan, and project best practices. Produces a structured review report with severity ratings. This skill is strictly read-only and does not modify any files.\n   9→\n  10→## Commands\n  11→\n  12→### prizmkit.code-review\n  13→\n  14→Review implemented code against spec and plan.\n  15→\n  16→**PRECONDITION:** `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md` exist in `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` with completed tasks\n  17→\n  18→**STEPS:**\n  19→\n  20→1. Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md` as review baseline\n  21→2. Read `.prizm-docs/root.prizm` RULES for project conventions\n  22→3. Scan all code files referenced in completed tasks\n  23→4. Review across 6 dimensions:\n  24→   - **Spec compliance**: Does code implement all acceptance criteria?\n  25→   - **Plan adherence**: Does implementation follow architectural decisions?\n  26→   - **Code quality**: Naming, structure, complexity, DRY\n  27→   - **Security**: Common vulnerabilities (injection, auth, data exposure)\n  28→   - **Consistency**: Follows project patterns from `.prizm-docs/` PATTERNS\n  29→   - **Test coverage**: Are critical paths tested?\n  30→5. Generate findings with severity: `CRITICAL` > `HIGH` > `MEDIUM` > `LOW`\n  31→6. Max 30 findings\n  32→7. Verdict: `PASS` | `PASS WITH WARNINGS` | `NEEDS FIXES`\n  33→8. OUTPUT: Structured review report (to conversation only, NOT written to file)\n  34→\n  35→**KEY RULES:**\n  36→- This is STRICTLY READ-ONLY — does NOT modify any files\n  37→- Output goes to conversation ONLY, not to any file\n  38→- Max 30 findings to keep review actionable\n  39→- Every CRITICAL finding MUST include a specific fix suggestion\n  40→- Spec compliance failures are always rated HIGH or CRITICAL\n  41→- Security findings are always rated HIGH or CRITICAL\n  42→\n  43→**VERDICT CRITERIA:**\n  44→- `PASS`: No CRITICAL or HIGH findings\n  45→- `PASS WITH WARNINGS`: No CRITICAL findings, some HIGH findings\n  46→- `NEEDS FIXES`: Any CRITICAL findings present\n  47→\n  48→**HANDOFF:** `prizmkit.summarize` (if PASS) or `prizmkit.implement` (if NEEDS FIXES)\n  49→\n  50→## Output\n  51→\n  52→Review report is output to conversation only. No files are created or modified.\n  53→\n  54→**Report Format:**\n  55→```\n  56→## Code Review: [Feature Name]\n  57→\n  58→### Summary\n  59→- Files reviewed: N\n  60→- Findings: N (Critical: N, High: N, Medium: N, Low: N)\n  61→- Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH WARNINGS | NEEDS FIXES]\n  62→\n  63→### Findings\n  64→\n  65→#### [SEVERITY] Finding Title\n  66→- File: path/to/file:line\n  67→- Dimension: [spec-compliance | plan-adherence | code-quality | security | consistency | test-coverage]\n  68→- Description: [What was found]\n  69→- Suggestion: [How to fix]\n  70→```\n  71→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde79226b7f9284963f7a13e6c2d6","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:58:39.561Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"99a1a291-4691-44e6-89a3-22cfb2176386","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde7ad7a46db4a4e4cbb2d6b920fc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-004: Pipeline Process Controller — Technical Plan\n   2→\n   3→## 1. Architecture Overview\n   4→\n   5→```\n   6→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   7→│                         Telegram Command Router (F-002)                      │\n   8→│                    src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js                            │\n   9→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  10→                                      │\n  11→                                      ▼\n  12→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  13→│                      Pipeline Controller (NEW)                               │\n  14→│                    src/services/pipeline-controller.js                       │\n  15→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n  16→│  │ • startPipeline()  • stopPipeline()  • retryTarget()                │    │\n  17→│  │ • runSingle()      • getStatus()      • getLogs()                   │    │\n  18→│  │ • forceUnlock()    • acquireLock()    • releaseLock()               │    │\n  19→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n  20→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  21→                    │                      │                      │\n  22→                    ▼                      ▼                      ▼\n  23→┌─────────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────┐\n  24→│    Lock Manager (NEW)   │ │   State Manager (NEW)   │ │   Script Runner     │\n  25→│  src/pipeline-infra/    │ │  src/pipeline-infra/    │ │    (Existing)       │\n  26→│    lock-manager.js      │ │    state-manager.js     │ │  script-runner.js   │\n  27→├─────────────────────────┤ ├─────────────────────────┤ ├─────────────────────┤\n  28→│ • acquireLock()         │ │ • readDaemonMeta()      │ │ • buildPipelineCmd()│\n  29→│ • releaseLock()         │ │ • readPipelineState()   │ │ • executePipeline() │\n  30→│ • isLocked()            │ │ • readCurrentSession()  │ │ • normalizeResult() │\n  31→│ • forceUnlock()         │ │ • writeDaemonMeta()     │ │                     │\n  32→│ • validateLock()        │ │ • getLastResult()       │ │                     │\n  33→└─────────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────┘\n  34→                    │                      │                      │\n  35→                    └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘\n  36→                                           ▼\n  37→                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  38→                    │                  dev-pipeline/scripts/                  │\n  39→                    │  launch-daemon.sh, launch-bugfix-daemon.sh              │\n  40→                    │  run.sh, run-bugfix.sh, retry-*.sh, reset-*.sh          │\n  41→                    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  42→                                           │\n  43→                                           ▼\n  44→                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  45→                    │                       State Files                       │\n  46→                    │  state/.pipeline.pid, state/pipeline.json               │\n  47→                    │  state/.pipeline-meta.json, state/pipeline-daemon.log   │\n  48→                    │  bugfix-state/... (mirror structure)                    │\n  49→                    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  50→```\n  51→\n  52→---\n  53→\n  54→## 2. Component Design\n  55→\n  56→### 2.1 Pipeline Controller (`src/services/pipeline-controller.js`)\n  57→\n  58→**职责**: 高层控制 API 入口，协调 lock-manager、state-manager、script-runner\n  59→\n  60→**核心方法**:\n  61→\n  62→```javascript\n  63→export function createPipelineController(options = {}) {\n  64→  const {\n  65→    lockManager = createLockManager(),\n  66→    stateManager = createStateManager(),\n  67→    scriptRunner = executePipelineCommand,\n  68→    config = loadPipelineInfraConfig()\n  69→  } = options;\n  70→\n  71→  return {\n  72→    // Lifecycle\n  73→    startPipeline(params),\n  74→    stopPipeline(params),\n  75→    \n  76→    // Target Operations\n  77→    retryTarget(params),\n  78→    runSingle(params),\n  79→    \n  80→    // Query\n  81→    getStatus(params),\n  82→    getLogs(params),\n  83→    \n  84→    // Admin\n  85→    forceUnlock(params),\n  86→    \n  87→    // Internal\n  88→    _acquireLock(type),\n  89→    _releaseLock(type),\n  90→  };\n  91→}\n  92→```\n  93→\n  94→### 2.2 Lock Manager (`src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js`)\n  95→\n  96→**职责**: 并发锁管理，防止同类型管道同时运行\n  97→\n  98→**实现策略**: 文件锁 + PID 校验\n  99→- 锁文件: `state/.pipeline.lock` / `bugfix-state/.pipeline.lock`\n 100→- 锁内容: `{ pid, acquiredAt, type }`\n 101→- 校验: 检查锁文件 + 验证 PID 是否存活\n 102→\n 103→**核心方法**:\n 104→\n 105→```javascript\n 106→export function createLockManager(options = {}) {\n 107→  const { config = loadPipelineInfraConfig() } = options;\n 108→  \n 109→  return {\n 110→    async acquireLock(type, pid = process.pid),\n 111→    async releaseLock(type, pid = process.pid),\n 112→    async isLocked(type),\n 113→    async validateLock(type),\n 114→    async forceUnlock(type),\n 115→    async getLockInfo(type),\n 116→  };\n 117→}\n 118→```\n 119→\n 120→### 2.3 State Manager (`src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js`)\n 121→\n 122→**职责**: 读取和管理管道状态文件\n 123→\n 124→**核心方法**:\n 125→\n 126→```javascript\n 127→export function createStateManager(options = {}) {\n 128→  const { config = loadPipelineInfraConfig() } = options;\n 129→  \n 130→  return {\n 131→    // Read Operations\n 132→    async readDaemonMeta(type),\n 133→    async readPipelineState(type),\n 134→    async readCurrentSession(type),\n 135→    async getLastResult(type),\n 136→    \n 137→    // Write Operations\n 138→    async writeDaemonMeta(type, meta),\n 139→    async writeLastResult(type, result),\n 140→    \n 141→    // Query\n 142→    async isDaemonRunning(type),\n 143→    async getDaemonPid(type),\n 144→  };\n 145→}\n 146→```\n 147→\n 148→### 2.4 Error Codes Extension (`src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`)\n 149→\n 150→**新增错误码**:\n 151→\n 152→```javascript\n 153→export const INFRA_ERROR_CODES = Object.freeze({\n 154→  // Existing\n 155→  CONFIG_MISSING: 'CONFIG_MISSING',\n 156→  CONFIG_INVALID: 'CONFIG_INVALID',\n 157→  PATH_INVALID: 'PATH_INVALID',\n 158→  SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND: 'SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND',\n 159→  EXEC_TIMEOUT: 'EXEC_TIMEOUT',\n 160→  EXEC_FAILED: 'EXEC_FAILED',\n 161→  \n 162→  // NEW for F-004\n 163→  LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED: 'LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED',\n 164→  ALREADY_STOPPED: 'ALREADY_STOPPED',\n 165→  PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING: 'PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING',\n 166→  INVALID_TARGET: 'INVALID_TARGET',\n 167→  TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE: 'TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE',\n 168→  DAEMON_START_FAILED: 'DAEMON_START_FAILED',\n 169→});\n 170→```\n 171→\n 172→---\n 173→\n 174→## 3. Interface Design\n 175→\n 176→### 3.1 Pipeline Controller API\n 177→\n 178→#### `startPipeline(params)`\n 179→\n 180→**Input**:\n 181→```typescript\n 182→interface StartPipelineParams {\n 183→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 184→  targetId?: string;        // Optional: start with specific target\n 185→  listPath?: string;        // Optional: override default list path\n 186→  daemon?: boolean;         // Default: true for startPipeline\n 187→  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 188→  timeoutMs?: number;\n 189→}\n 190→```\n 191→\n 192→**Output**:\n 193→```typescript\n 194→interface PipelineResult {\n 195→  ok: boolean;\n 196→  runId?: string;\n 197→  pid?: number;\n 198→  message: string;\n 199→  errorCode?: string;\n 200→  hint?: string;\n 201→  context?: Record<string, unknown>;\n 202→}\n 203→```\n 204→\n 205→**Behavior**:\n 206→1. Acquire lock for pipeline type\n 207→2. If daemon mode, call `launch-daemon.sh start`\n 208→3. If foreground, call `run.sh run [targetId]`\n 209→4. Return result with PID (daemon) or execution result (foreground)\n 210→\n 211→---\n 212→\n 213→#### `stopPipeline(params)`\n 214→\n 215→**Input**:\n 216→```typescript\n 217→interface StopPipelineParams {\n 218→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 219→  timeoutMs?: number;       // Default: 10000\n 220→}\n 221→```\n 222→\n 223→**Output**:\n 224→```typescript\n 225→interface StopResult {\n 226→  ok: boolean;\n 227→  previousPid?: number;\n 228→  message: string;\n 229→  errorCode?: string;\n 230→}\n 231→```\n 232→\n 233→**Behavior**:\n 234→1. Check if daemon is running\n 235→2. Call `launch-daemon.sh stop`\n 236→3. Wait for process termination (with timeout)\n 237→4. Release lock\n 238→5. Return previous PID and status\n 239→\n 240→---\n 241→\n 242→#### `retryTarget(params)`\n 243→\n 244→**Input**:\n 245→```typescript\n 246→interface RetryTargetParams {\n 247→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 248→  targetId: string;\n 249→  listPath?: string;\n 250→  daemon?: boolean;\n 251→  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 252→}\n 253→```\n 254→\n 255→**Output**: Same as `startPipeline()`\n 256→\n 257→**Behavior**:\n 258→1. Validate target exists and is retryable\n 259→2. If daemon mode, acquire lock first\n 260→3. Execute retry script\n 261→4. Return result\n 262→\n 263→---\n 264→\n 265→#### `runSingle(params)`\n 266→\n 267→**Input**:\n 268→```typescript\n 269→interface RunSingleParams {\n 270→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 271→  targetId: string;\n 272→  listPath?: string;\n 273→  timeoutMs?: number;\n 274→  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n 275→}\n 276→```\n 277→\n 278→**Output**:\n 279→```typescript\n 280→interface RunSingleResult {\n 281→  ok: boolean;\n 282→  targetId: string;\n 283→  message: string;\n 284→  stdout?: string;\n 285→  stderr?: string;\n 286→  exitCode?: number;\n 287→  errorCode?: string;\n 288→}\n 289→```\n 290→\n 291→**Behavior**:\n 292→1. Execute single target in foreground\n 293→2. Do NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n 294→3. Return full execution details\n 295→\n 296→---\n 297→\n 298→#### `getStatus(params)`\n 299→\n 300→**Input**:\n 301→```typescript\n 302→interface GetStatusParams {\n 303→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 304→}\n 305→```\n 306→\n 307→**Output**:\n 308→```typescript\n 309→interface StatusResult {\n 310→  ok: boolean;\n 311→  isRunning: boolean;\n 312→  pid?: number;\n 313→  currentFeature?: string;\n 314→  startedAt?: string;\n 315→  lastResult?: LastResult;\n 316→  lockInfo?: LockInfo;\n 317→  message: string;\n 318→}\n 319→\n 320→interface LastResult {\n 321→  runId: string;\n 322→  completedAt: string;\n 323→  status: 'success' | 'failed' | 'partial';\n 324→  featuresTotal: number;\n 325→  featuresCompleted: number;\n 326→}\n 327→\n 328→interface LockInfo {\n 329→  pid: number;\n 330→  acquiredAt: string;\n 331→}\n 332→```\n 333→\n 334→---\n 335→\n 336→#### `getLogs(params)`\n 337→\n 338→**Input**:\n 339→```typescript\n 340→interface GetLogsParams {\n 341→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 342→  lines?: number;           // Default: 100\n 343→  follow?: boolean;         // Not implemented in v1\n 344→}\n 345→```\n 346→\n 347→**Output**:\n 348→```typescript\n 349→interface LogsResult {\n 350→  ok: boolean;\n 351→  logs: string;\n 352→  logPath: string;\n 353→  lines: number;\n 354→  message: string;\n 355→}\n 356→```\n 357→\n 358→---\n 359→\n 360→#### `forceUnlock(params)`\n 361→\n 362→**Input**:\n 363→```typescript\n 364→interface ForceUnlockParams {\n 365→  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n 366→}\n 367→```\n 368→\n 369→**Output**:\n 370→```typescript\n 371→interface ForceUnlockResult {\n 372→  ok: boolean;\n 373→  previousPid?: number;\n 374→  message: string;\n 375→}\n 376→```\n 377→\n 378→**Behavior**:\n 379→1. Get lock info\n 380→2. Remove lock file\n 381→3. Return previous lock info\n 382→\n 383→---\n 384→\n 385→### 3.2 Lock Manager API\n 386→\n 387→#### `acquireLock(type, pid?)`\n 388→\n 389→**Input**:\n 390→- `type`: 'feature' | 'bugfix'\n 391→- `pid`: number (default: process.pid)\n 392→\n 393→**Output**:\n 394→```typescript\n 395→interface LockResult {\n 396→  ok: boolean;\n 397→  lockPath: string;\n 398→  errorCode?: 'LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED';\n 399→  currentHolder?: LockInfo;\n 400→}\n 401→```\n 402→\n 403→**Implementation**:\n 404→1. Check if lock file exists\n 405→2. If exists, validate PID is dead\n 406→3. Write lock file atomically\n 407→4. Return result\n 408→\n 409→---\n 410→\n 411→### 3.3 State Manager API\n 412→\n 413→#### `readDaemonMeta(type)`\n 414→\n 415→**Output**:\n 416→```typescript\n 417→interface DaemonMeta {\n 418→  pid: number;\n 419→  started_at: string;\n 420→  feature_list: string;\n 421→  env_overrides: string;\n 422→  log_file: string;\n 423→}\n 424→```\n 425→\n 426→#### `readPipelineState(type)`\n 427→\n 428→**Output**:\n 429→```typescript\n 430→interface PipelineState {\n 431→  run_id: string;\n 432→  status: 'running' | 'paused' | 'completed' | 'failed';\n 433→  feature_list_path: string;\n 434→  created_at: string;\n 435→  total_features: number;\n 436→  completed_features: number;\n 437→  paused_at?: string;\n 438→}\n 439→```\n 440→\n 441→#### `isDaemonRunning(type)`\n 442→\n 443→**Output**: `boolean`\n 444→\n 445→**Implementation**:\n 446→1. Read daemon meta\n 447→2. Check if PID is alive via `process.kill(pid, 0)`\n 448→3. Return boolean\n 449→\n 450→---\n 451→\n 452→## 4. Data Model\n 453→\n 454→### 4.1 Lock File Schema\n 455→\n 456→**Path**: `{stateDir}/.pipeline.lock` or `bugfix-state/.pipeline.lock`\n 457→\n 458→```json\n 459→{\n 460→  \"pid\": 12345,\n 461→  \"acquiredAt\": \"2026-03-12T10:30:00Z\",\n 462→  \"type\": \"feature\",\n 463→  \"hostname\": \"dev-machine\"\n 464→}\n 465→```\n 466→\n 467→### 4.2 Last Result Schema (NEW)\n 468→\n 469→**Path**: `{stateDir}/.last-result.json` or `bugfix-state/.last-result.json`\n 470→\n 471→```json\n 472→{\n 473→  \"runId\": \"run-20260312-103000\",\n 474→  \"completedAt\": \"2026-03-12T12:45:00Z\",\n 475→  \"status\": \"success\",\n 476→  \"featuresTotal\": 8,\n 477→  \"featuresCompleted\": 8,\n 478→  \"exitCode\": 0,\n 479→  \"message\": \"Pipeline completed successfully\"\n 480→}\n 481→```\n 482→\n 483→### 4.3 State File Integration\n 484→\n 485→Reuse existing state files:\n 486→- `state/pipeline.json` → `readPipelineState('feature')`\n 487→- `state/.pipeline-meta.json` → `readDaemonMeta('feature')`\n 488→- `state/current-session.json` → `readCurrentSession('feature')`\n 489→- Mirror paths for `bugfix-state/`\n 490→\n 491→---\n 492→\n 493→## 5. Module Dependencies\n 494→\n 495→```\n 496→pipeline-controller.js\n 497→    ├── lock-manager.js\n 498→    ├── state-manager.js\n 499→    ├── script-runner.js (existing)\n 500→    ├── config-loader.js (existing)\n 501→    └── error-codes.js (extended)\n 502→\n 503→lock-manager.js\n 504→    ├── path-policy.js (existing)\n 505→    └── config-loader.js (existing)\n 506→\n 507→state-manager.js\n 508→    ├── path-policy.js (existing)\n 509→    └── config-loader.js (existing)\n 510→```\n 511→\n 512→---\n 513→\n 514→## 6. Testing Strategy\n 515→\n 516→### 6.1 Unit Tests\n 517→\n 518→| Module | Test File | Focus |\n 519→|--------|-----------|-------|\n 520→| lock-manager.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` | Lock acquire/release, PID validation, stale lock cleanup |\n 521→| state-manager.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js` | State file reading, JSON parsing, missing file handling |\n 522→| pipeline-controller.js | `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js` | All API methods, error handling, mock dependencies |\n 523→| error-codes.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/error-codes.test.js` | Error code validation, error factory |\n 524→\n 525→### 6.2 Integration Tests\n 526→\n 527→**File**: `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n 528→\n 529→| Test Case | Description |\n 530→|-----------|-------------|\n 531→| Full Lifecycle | startPipeline → getStatus → stopPipeline |\n 532→| Lock Behavior | Concurrent start attempts, lock release on stop |\n 533→| Error Recovery | Stop non-running pipeline, retry invalid target |\n 534→| State Persistence | Verify state files after operations |\n 535→| Daemon Mode | Start daemon, query PID, verify log output |\n 536→\n 537→### 6.3 Test Coverage Target\n 538→\n 539→- Core modules: > 90% branch coverage\n 540→- Integration tests: All user stories covered\n 541→\n 542→---\n 543→\n 544→## 7. Risk Assessment\n 545→\n 546→| Risk | Mitigation | Owner |\n 547→|------|------------|-------|\n 548→| Lock file corruption | Atomic write via temp file + rename, validate JSON on read | Dev |\n 549→| PID reuse race condition | Include timestamp in lock, validate with short timeout | Dev |\n 550→| Large log file blocking | Use `fs.createReadStream` with line limit | Dev |\n 551→| Test environment isolation | Use temp directories for state files in tests | Dev |\n 552→| Backward compatibility with existing scripts | No script modifications, only wrappers | Dev |\n 553→\n 554→---\n 555→\n 556→## 8. User Story to Component Mapping\n 557→\n 558→| User Story | Primary Component | Supporting Components |\n 559→|------------|-------------------|----------------------|\n 560→| US-1: Unified Pipeline Start | pipeline-controller.startPipeline() | lock-manager, script-runner |\n 561→| US-2: Pipeline Stop | pipeline-controller.stopPipeline() | state-manager, lock-manager |\n 562→| US-3: Target Retry | pipeline-controller.retryTarget() | script-runner, state-manager |\n 563→| US-4: Run Single Feature | pipeline-controller.runSingle() | script-runner |\n 564→| US-5: Status Query | pipeline-controller.getStatus() | state-manager, lock-manager |\n 565→| US-6: Logs Query | pipeline-controller.getLogs() | state-manager |\n 566→| US-7: Concurrency Protection | lock-manager | state-manager |\n 567→| US-8: Error Mapping | error-codes.js (extended) | pipeline-controller |\n 568→| US-9: Telegram Handler Integration | pipeline-controller API design | All |\n 569→\n 570→**Mapping Notes:**\n 571→- US-2 → stopPipeline: 停止守护进程\n 572→- US-3 → retryTarget: 重试失败目标\n 573→- US-5 → getStatus: 状态查询\n 574→- US-6 → getLogs: 日志查询\n 575→- US-7 → lock-manager: 并发保护\n 576→- US-8 → error-codes.js: 错误映射\n 577→- US-9 → API design: Telegram 集成\n 578→\n 579→---\n 580→\n 581→## 9. Implementation Phases\n 582→\n 583→### Phase 1: Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n 584→- Setup test infrastructure\n 585→- Extend error codes\n 586→- Create lock-manager\n 587→- Create state-manager\n 588→\n 589→### Phase 2: Core Controller (T-010 ~ T-099)\n 590→- Implement pipeline-controller skeleton\n 591→- Implement each API method\n 592→- Integrate with existing script-runner\n 593→\n 594→### Phase 3: User Story Implementation (T-100+)\n 595→- US-1: startPipeline\n 596→- US-2: stopPipeline\n 597→- US-3: retryTarget\n 598→- US-4: runSingle\n 599→- US-5: getStatus\n 600→- US-6: getLogs\n 601→- US-7: Lock integration\n 602→- US-8: Error mapping\n 603→- US-9: Integration tests\n 604→\n 605→### Phase 4: Polish (T-900+)\n 606→- Documentation updates\n 607→- Performance optimization\n 608→- Edge case handling\n 609→\n 610→---\n 611→\n 612→## 10. Key Decisions\n 613→\n 614→| ID | Decision | Rationale |\n 615→|----|----------|-----------|\n 616→| D1 | 文件锁 + PID 校验实现并发保护 | 避免引入外部依赖，满足 AC-7.3 (进程异常退出时自动释放锁) |\n 617→| D2 | Separate lock-manager module | Single responsibility, easier testing |\n 618→| D3 | Reuse existing state files | Backward compatible, no migration needed |\n 619→| D4 | New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service | Clear separation, avoid breaking existing API |\n 620→| D5 | runSingle does NOT acquire lock | Independent execution use case |\n 621→| D6 | Last result stored in separat