{"type":"user","uuid":"9675bd4d-3142-4f1a-a26a-add3c67e3e3a","session_id":"e8c5e130-cc78-4ab4-9f64-924bbfd756be","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde79226b7f9284963f7a13e6c2d6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All extended integration tests pass. Let me provide the final code review summary:\n\n---\n\n## Code Review: F-004 Pipeline Process Controller\n\n### Summary\n- **Files reviewed:** 8\n- **Findings:** 8 (Critical: 0, High: 0, Medium: 5, Low: 3)\n- **Verdict:** ✅ **PASS**\n\n---\n\n### Test Results\n\n| Test File | Tests | Status |\n|-----------|-------|--------|\n| `lock-manager.test.js` | 16 | ✅ All Pass |\n| `state-manager.test.js` | 20 | ✅ All Pass |\n| `pipeline-controller.test.js` | 23 | ✅ All Pass |\n| `f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js` | 15 | ✅ All Pass |\n| `f004-extended.integration.test.js` | 14 | ✅ All Pass |\n| **Total** | **88** | ✅ All Pass |\n\n---\n\n### Spec Compliance Matrix\n\n| User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Status |\n|------------|---------------------|--------|\n| US-1: Unified Pipeline Start | AC-1.1 ~ AC-1.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-2: Pipeline Stop | AC-2.1 ~ AC-2.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-3: Target Retry | AC-3.1 ~ AC-3.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-4: Run Single Feature | AC-4.1 ~ AC-4.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-5: Status Query | AC-5.1 ~ AC-5.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-6: Logs Query | AC-6.1 ~ AC-6.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-7: Concurrency Protection | AC-7.1 ~ AC-7.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-8: Error Mapping | AC-8.1 ~ AC-8.4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-9: Telegram Handler Integration | AC-9.1 ~ AC-9.4 | ✅ PASS |\n\n---\n\n### Findings\n\n| Severity | Finding | Dimension |\n|----------|---------|-----------|\n| MEDIUM | Potential TOCTOU race condition in lock acquisition | security |\n| MEDIUM | Duplicate log reading logic in controller and state-manager | code-quality |\n| MEDIUM | Silent error suppression in lock file read catch block | code-quality |\n| MEDIUM | Missing script path in SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND error context | spec-compliance |\n| MEDIUM | Incomplete NFR performance tests (T-905 ~ T-914) | plan-adherence |\n| LOW | Unused `getStatusIcon` function in status.js | code-quality |\n| LOW | Inconsistent JSDoc style across methods | consistency |\n| LOW | ALREADY_STOPPED returns `ok: true` with errorCode | spec-compliance |\n\n---\n\n### Plan Adherence\n\nThe implementation follows the architectural decisions from `plan.md`:\n- ✅ D1: File lock + PID validation (implemented in `lock-manager.js`)\n- ✅ D2: Separate `pipeline-controller.js` module (not extending existing service)\n- ✅ D3: Reuse existing state files (backward compatible)\n- ✅ D4: New module with clear separation\n- ✅ D5: `runSingle` does NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n- ✅ D6: Last result stored in separate file (`.last-result.json`)\n\n---\n\n### Integration Test Coverage\n\nThe integration tests cover all 9 user stories:\n\n| Test Case | User Story | Description |\n|-----------|------------|-------------|\n| US-1 startPipeline daemon mode | US-1 | Full lifecycle with daemon |\n| US-1 startPipeline foreground mode | US-1 | Non-daemon execution |\n| US-2 stopPipeline | US-2 | Stop running daemon |\n| US-2 ALREADY_STOPPED | US-2 | Stop non-running pipeline |\n| US-3 retryTarget | US-3 | Retry failed target |\n| US-4 runSingle | US-4 | Single target execution |\n| US-5 getStatus | US-5 | Status query with all fields |\n| US-6 getLogs | US-6 | Log retrieval |\n| US-7 concurrent start attempts | US-7 | Lock behavior test |\n| US-7 forceUnlock | US-7 | Admin unlock operation |\n| US-8 error codes | US-8 | Structured error validation |\n| US-9 JSON serialization | US-9 | Telegram compatibility |\n\n**Extended tests add coverage for:**\n- Cross-module data flow\n- Boundary conditions (empty/long targetId, log line limits)\n- Error paths (script exceptions, corrupted files)\n- Concurrency edge cases\n- Large log file performance\n- Feature/bugfix type parity\n\n---\n\n### COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n\n**Reviewer Agent** has completed Phase 6 review for F-004.\n\n**Verdict:** ✅ **PASS**\n\n- No CRITICAL or HIGH findings\n- All 9 user stories implemented and tested\n- 88 tests pass across unit and integration suites\n- Implementation follows plan.md architectural decisions\n- Code quality is good with minor improvements noted\n\n**Follow-up items (non-blocking):**\n1. Consider race condition mitigation in lock acquisition\n2. Deduplicate log reading logic\n3. Complete NFR performance tests (T-905 ~ T-914) as tech debt\n\n[Agent ID: agent-8125d461]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde79226b7f9284963f7a13e6c2d6","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:00:45.946Z","_requestId":"e21d0cf101524861bfec5442101833c9"}
